title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water, lemon juice and salt.
Cool.
Grind onion and pepper; drain off all juice.
Mix onion and pepper with cottage cheese, mayonnaise and nuts.
Combine the two mixtures and place in a mold to chill and set.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Simmer onions with skins on until tender.
Cool slightly and peel.
Saute
celery
in
butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper, milk,
cream
and
the onions.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.
Add almonds, paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sandy's lazy cabbage rolls
directions: Brown ground beef with onion soup mix.
Add rice.
Put cabbage into casserole dish.
Mix water and soup.
Put meat mixture on top of cabbage.
Pour water and soup mixture over all.
Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid together with sugar, ReaLemon and Punch.
Before serving, pour ginger ale into mixture.
Ready to serve.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream shortening and cream cheese; blend yolk and add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add flour.
Top with cherry or nut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
It is best to double this recipe.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight, then serve.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Leave in pan when done.
Pour glaze over cake and let cake soak up glaze before removing from pan.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Add melted butter to cornbread crumbs; toss with fork to mix thoroughly.
Toast in skillet over low heat until golden brown. Combine apples, sugar, salt and spices; mix well.
Spread a layer of toasted crumbs in bottom of 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.

title: braised swiss steak
directions: Wipe steak with damp paper towels. Combine crumbs, salt and pepper.
Place steak on wooden board.
Sprinkle half of crumb mixture on steak and pound.
Turn over and repeat.
Cut steak into 6 portions.

title: basic omelet(microwave)
directions: In a 2-cup measure, beat well the eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Preheat the browning grill according to manufacturer's instructions on High.
Spread butter on preheated browning grill and pour on egg mixture.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on Medium-high (roast). Top with cheese. Fold omelet and let stand 30 to 40 seconds or until cheese is melted.

title: rachel's barbecue beef
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the beef.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Pour over beef.
Cook in a 300° oven for 6 to 7 hours. Remove beef bones. Pull meat into shreds.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: noodles lorraine
directions: Cook noodles according to directions. Drain.

In a small pan, melt butter and cook onion until transparent. Combine eggs, salt and nutmeg in a large bowl. Add noodles, butter, onion, bacon and cheese. Place in 2-quart baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 350° (until golden brown).

title: zucchini custard
directions: Sprinkle zucchini with salt; set aside for 1 hour.
Place in colander; press out liquid.
Thoroughly blend zucchini, cheese, pepper, garlic, parsley, biscuit mix and eggs.
In 10-inch glass dish melt butter on High 30 seconds.
Add zucchini mixture. Microwave on High uncovered for 10 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking.
Rest 5 minutes.
Top with chives.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix well boiled water and sugar; cool it. Mix all and let stand 2 to 4 weeks.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Mix soda with 2 tablespoons hot oil, then blend.
Add all ingredients together and bake 20 minutes in greased pan at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, salt, egg yolks, flour and milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thickened, then add margarine and lemon extract.
Alternate layers of wafers, sliced bananas and filling. Can put beaten egg whites over top and brown.
Sprinkle crushed wafers on top.

title: hot fudge chocolate syrup
directions: Stir all ingredients thoroughly.
May be refrigerated and "zapped" in microwave later.
You can heat the syrup on low heat on top of the stove.
Use as topping for ice cream or cake.

title: chicken in "maple cream"
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine egg and milk.
Put chicken pieces into this mixture and roll in crumbs.
Brown chicken in hot oil and place pieces in shallow baking pan.
Combine milk, cream and maple syrup.
Pour this over the chicken.

title: gourmet rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter in saucepan.
Stir in rice and beef stock (omit the herb and seasonings packet).
Put rice mixture into deep Pyrex dish.
Bake 1 hour.

title: mrs. olson's apple crisp
directions: Place the sliced and peeled apples into a greased dish. Sprinkle with the lemon juice, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar. Combine the brown sugar, flour, oatmeal, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Add the melted butter; mix until crumbly. Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of apples; do not pat down.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes, or until apples are tender.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Set aside 6 strawberries.
Puree remaining strawberries and strain into 4 quart saucepan.
Add orange juice.
In small bowl mix tapioca with 4 tablespoons puree, add to pan with spices. Heat, stirring constantly and boil until thick (about 1 minute). Remove from heat.
Pour soup into large bowl.
Add sugar, lemon peel, juice, and buttermilk.
Blend well.
Fold reserved strawberries into soup and chill at least 8 hours.
Serve in melons garnished with lemon slices if desired.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add onions, basil, thyme and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste, water, 1/4 cup cheese, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Combine with spaghetti.
Pour into 2-quart 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir before serving.

title: coq au vin
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil mixed with red wine.
Add onion, garlic and seasonings.
Remove chicken and add remaining ingredients.
Return chicken to pan and bake in 350° oven until tender.

title: betty's spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in olive oil until soft white.
Season meat; add and brown lightly.
Add rest of ingredients; cook over low flame for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Slightly thaw bread dough. Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle nuts on bottom.
Cut 1 loaf of bread in 12 equal pieces. Lay in bottom of pan.
In pan, mix vanilla pudding, brown sugar and milk.
Heat through.
Pour over bread in pan. Cut second loaf in 12 equal pieces and place on top of pudding mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a greased and floured square pan at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into a skillet.
Makes 1 large skillet and 1 small.
Bake 30 minutes or until center is done.

title: cheese potato scallop
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender. Drain well. Melt 1/2 c butter in large saucepan. Add onion; saute until tender. Blend in flour, salt, dry mustard and worcestershire. Gradually stir in milk. Cook stirring constantly. until sauce thickens and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add cheese and stir until melted. Place potatoes in a baking dish. Pour on cheese sauce. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs, combined with 1/4 c melted butter. Top with paprika. Bake at 350 decrees for 30 minutes.

title: pear preserves
directions: Sprinkle sugar over pears.
Cover and let set overnight.
Cook on medium heat for 45 minutes or until thick.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Combine everything and mix well.
Fold into a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mocha chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening and butter in a large mixing bowl at medium speed of an electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and powdered sugar, beating well.
Add egg, beating well. Dissolve coffee granules in water; add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Stir in chocolate morsels and pecans.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls; roll in additional sugar.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets. Press with a fork to flatten.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.
Yield:
6 1/2 dozen.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Combine vegetables with garlic and salt; cover with crushed ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Allow to stand at room temperature 3 hours; rinse and drain well. Discard garlic.
Heat remaining ingredients in large saucepan to boiling.
Add vegetables; heat to boiling.
Remove; fill hot sterilized pint jars with hot vegetables and liquid, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal and process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: no name cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and water.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar and pour over crust. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts with cheese sauce
directions: Arrange chicken (skin up) in large broiler-proof dish; top with 1 piece of bacon and bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes or until bacon is crisp and chicken is cooked.
Spoon off fat.

title: aunt patty's bean casserole
directions: *Can use larger than 16-ounce size if you like.

title: chicken-andouille gumbo
directions: Make roux by slowly browning the flour in the shortening; when golden brown, add onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook at low heat until the vegetables separate form the shortening.
In another pan, brown the cut up hen in some extra shortening, using enough to seer chicken well.
Add hen to the brown roux mixture and cook together for a few minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: beef tips
directions: Place beef tips, uncooked, in crock-pot.
Add soups and about 3/4 can of water.
Stir.
Cook on high for 3 to 4 hours, until beef is tender.
You can also bake this in oven at 350° for about 2 hours.
Serve over cooked pasta or rice.

title: my mom's easy, delicious potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Spritz Pam in bottom of casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper by hand until creamy. Slice potatoes. Layer, starting with sliced potatoes to cover bottom.
Pour 1/2 of the soup mixture over the potatoes.
Cover with sliced cheese. (You usually have about 2 layers worth; always end with cheese.)
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°. This recipe can be adjusted to serve 6 to 15 by doubling recipe and using a larger, 9 x 13-inch, pan.

title: spiced pineapple chunks
directions: Drain pineapple; add ingredients to juice in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Add pineapple chunks to mixture and bring to a boil again. Set aside until cool, then remove cinnamon stick. Food coloring may also be added to the mixture. Chill in refrigerator. Serve with toothpicks.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a large mixing bowl until it is smooth.
Pour the batter into a greased and floured 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cream of butternut squash soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cream and rice.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Put in blender.
Return to pot.
Stir in cream and rice. Garnish with scallions.

title: spinach salad with roasted peanuts
directions: For dressing, combine oil, vinegar, soy sauce, honey mustard and dill weed in a jar.
Shake well.

title: magic mudd
directions: Mix until gels.
Let set until mixture feels dry to the touch. Pick up and squeeze.
Ooozy!

title: zucchini bread(makes 2 large loaves or 4 small loaves)
directions: To eggs, gradually add sugar.
Beat in remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Spread mixture into pie pan.
Next mix chili sauce and horseradish and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Add clams or flaked crabmeat to the top, garnish with parsley for color.

title: fried pies
directions: Cook fruit to your taste.
Let cool.
While cooking, mix flour and milk.
Sprinkle flour on table.
Roll out by the tablespoon as thin as you can in a circle.
Spoon in about a tablespoon of fruit. Fold over, then using a fork, press ends together using 9-inch iron skillet.
Heat oil.
When hot, put in pies, three at a time.
Cook until golden brown, then flip.
Do the same on other side.

title: poulet de normandy
directions: Mix stuffing and margarine in water; set aside. Combine onions, celery, mayonnaise, salt and mix well with bread mixture. Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Put 1/2 bread mixture, then spread chicken on top. Top with rest of bread mixture. Beat 2 eggs in milk; pour over mixture.
Refrigerate all night. Take out 2 hours before baking time.
Spread with mushroom soup. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Note:
Condensed milk takes the place of the sugar.

title: pink salad
directions: Boil pineapple.
Add jello; stir and chill.
Mix in Cool Whip and pecans.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cottage cheese on high 5 minutes.
Stir in yogurt and lemon peel.
Use strawberries, melon wedges, pineapple chunks, apples, etc., as dippers.

title: harvard beets
directions: Boil 6 to 8 small beets until tender.
Make a sauce of sugar, vinegar and cornstarch.
Boil slowly for 5 minutes.
Slice beets into the hot sauce; let stand 15 minutes on back of stove to bring out the color.

title: cheesy tuna bake
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Stir in soup that has been diluted with 1/2 can water.
Stir in cheese, cooked egg noodles, tuna fish and pimentos.
Put in buttered casserole dish. Top casserole with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.

title: seven layer bars or hello dolly bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).

In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter in oven. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over melted butter. Pour sweetened condensed milk over the crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients. Press down firmly with fork. Bake 25 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: nachos
directions: Spread 1 teaspoon of refried beans or bean dip on each tortilla chip.
Top with one teaspoon of cheese and one thin slice of olive.
Place 8 in circle on paper plate.
Heat in microwave oven.
Use Level 7 for 30 to 45 seconds, or until cheese is melted.
Serve warm.
Repeat with remaining appetizers.

title: round steak with rich gravy
directions: Sprinkle 1 side of meat with half of the flour; pound in. Turn meat and pound in remaining flour.
Cut meat into 6 to 8 serving pieces.
Melt shortening in a large skillet; brown meat in shortening over medium heat for about 15 minutes.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over meat.
Add cream of mushroom soup and water.
Cover tightly; simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
Place meat on warm platter.

title: potatoes ala shirley
directions: Layer unpeeled potatoes in pan.
Melt butter.
Mix in onion soup, salt and water.
Pour over potatoes. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: kate's favorite jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add bananas, strawberries, and pineapple, undrained, and mix well.
Pour in bowl and chill until set.

title: larry's lo-cal pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add all the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into 12 muffin cups sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first three ingredients in small bowl.

title: orange froth drink
directions: Put all in blender and mix until frothy.

title: combination salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Combine and bring to a boil; pineapple juice and Jell-O.
Refrigerate until mixture has the consistency of syrup.
Blend in cream cheese, pimento, celery and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into baking dish and refrigerate until set.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and Crisco; add sugar then beaten eggs.
Into 1 cup of flour, sift soda and baking powder.
Add this to sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Turn onto a floured board; knead until smooth.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in any shape. Bake about 10 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: While cooking beans, melt butter.
Add flour.
To the mixture with heat off, add sugar, onion, pepper and salt.
Add above to sour cream; mix beans and cream mixture.
Top with cheese.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Can add a crumb topping of crushed corn flakes and 1 tablespoon melted butter.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Cut crab into small bite-size pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in small glass casserole. Great served warm on crackers.

title: low-fat cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine; mix well.
Pat bottom of 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan. Set aside.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Put all ingredients, except broth, in a large bowl.
Add boiling hot broth and stir until mixture is well blended.
You may need more broth.
Add a little at a time.

title: delicious pie
directions: Whip cream cheese & milk, fold in cool whip. Divide into 2 frozen Graham cracker pie shells. Toast pecans, coconut & butter at 300° until light brown (stir often). Sprinkle pecans & coconut on top of pies and top with butterscotch topping & freeze. Keep in freezer.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Mix flour, paprika, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Cut chicken into 1 to 1 1/2-inch squares; place in plastic bag and cover with flour mixture.
Brown chicken in 2 tablespoons oil. Put onion in pan.
Add water; cook, covered, on low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms; cook for 5 more minutes.
Add sour cream and lemon rind; reheat.
Serve with rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: bucket dessert
directions: Prepare pudding according to the directions.
Drop 1 layer into bottom of empty ice cream bucket and cover with half of pudding, 1/2 of Cool Whip and 2 candy bars, crumbled.
Bake cake following directions on box in 2 (8-inch) rounds.
Repeat by dropping 2 cake layers, pudding, Cool Whip and candy bars; cover and refrigerate.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Cook about 20 minutes until boiling; cover.
Reduce heat; simmer for 25 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, banana, marshmallows, coconut and almonds.
Fold in yogurt. Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: red top salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows and lemon Jell-O in boiling water.
Let cool.
Dissolve cherry Jell-O in 1 3/4 cups boiling water; chill until slightly thickened. Beat cheese, salt and mayonnaise in mixer until light.
Stir in celery, nuts and pineapple. Add marshmallow mixture and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Pour cherry Jell-O over it.

title: scotch cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, put margarine, shortening, cocoa and water; bring to a rapid boil. Pour into flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Make icing about 5 minutes before cake has finished baking.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar; add undrained, thawed strawberries.
Add bananas, nuts, Cool Whip and pineapple.
Mix and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze; thaw 15 minutes before serving.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until thickened.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and mix well.
Add grated rind, and juice of lemon, and 3 Tbsp. warm water. Cook mixture in double boiler to thick custard stage.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding 1/2 cup sugar gradually.
Fold into custard mixture.
Fill previously baked pie shell and brown in oven for a few minutes.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Add beaten eggs, milk, oil and peeled, finely chopped apples.
Stir until all ingredients are moistened.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut bacon slice in half.
Roll bacon around water chestnut slice.
Fasten with wooden toothpick.
Place on broiler pan and bake at 375° until bacon starts to brown, 20 minutes.
Remove and dip in barbecue sauce and bake until done, about 15 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add egg yolks.
Add vanilla to creamed mixture.
Add flour, baking powder and salt to graham cracker crumbs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to cream mixture.
Add nuts; beat well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan spurs or pralines
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, butter, salt and 2 cups cream.
Bring to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Add remaining cup of cream and cook slowly to firm ball at 234°.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool for awhile and add nuts.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet or on table lined with foil.
Let stand until cool!
Melt chocolate over hot water, then spread onto pralines.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13-inch pan:
flour, nuts and butter. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes; cool.
Cream together powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Beat well, then fold in 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread over baked crust.
Mix strawberries with glaze and spread on top.
Spread 3 cups Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Tear ham into small pieces.
Mix with liquids.
Slow cook in crock-pot for 6 to 7 hours.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl until well blended. Chill in refrigerator for several hours.
Makes a delicious dessert or cool salad plate addition.
Can also be made with strawberry jello and fresh or frozen strawberries.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook limas by directions on package.
When tender, add mushroom soup, grated cheese and chopped pimento.
Put in slightly greased (you may use Pam) casserole. Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, mushrooms and soup. Pour into baking pan.
Top with Durkee onions. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots until tender in small amount of water.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble.
Save 2 tablespoons bacon fat and saute onion and celery.
Combine onion, celery, salt, pepper and crumbled bacon.
Add to potatoes.
Add half and half and milk.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese and parsley on before serving.

title: garden vegetable medley(microwave)
directions: Break
cauliflower
into
flowerets;
cut
flowerets in half. Slice
flowerets
from
broccoli,
leaving
2 inches of stem. Arrange broccoli in circle around edge of 12-inch round platter with flowerets resting on rim.
Arrange cauliflower in inner circle.
Arrange
squash,
then
zucchini,
in circle in center. Place
red
pepper
in center.
Place butter in 1 cup measuring cup
and
cook
on High for 45 seconds.
Pour melted butter over vegetables.
Sprinkle
with
garlic salt and seasoned pepper. Cover with plastic wrap and cook on High 7 to 8 minutes or
until crisp but tender.
Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, 3 ounces milk and margarine.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Melt caramels with remaining 3 ounces milk.
Pour over cake mixture. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over caramel.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: strawberry squirt
directions: Blend berries and yogurt at high speed in the blender until smooth.
Stir in chilled Perrier.
This can also be frozen like a popsicle.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form loaf in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Rinse chicken under cold running water; blot dry.
Cut crosswise into 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch strips; set aside.
Then combine salt, pepper and flour in plastic bag and add half of chicken and shake to coat.
Repeat with remainder.

title: 24 hour 7 layer salad
directions: Break lettuce
in bottom of bowl.
Add in layers onion, celery,
peppers
and cooked peas.
Seal with mayonnaise.
Top mayo layer
with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Toss just before serving.

title: cheese and chilies
directions: Put chili peppers in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Pour cheeses, milk and egg mixture over chili and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: braised celery hearts
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil in medium saucepan over high flame.
Reduce flame, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove bay leaf and cloves; drain.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Beat eggs until light and add to sugar.
Mix bananas and lemon juice together and add to mixture. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and mix quickly into sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Stir together pineapple, sugar and flour.
Top with cheese, then cracker crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: old fashion stackcake
directions: Grease and flour iron skillet.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk to make thin.
Pour small amounts in pan to make thin layers. Bake at 350° for a short time.
Makes about 6 to 7 layers.
Spread applesauce or apple butter between each layer.

title: gail's famous chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups boiling water. Prepare stuffing as package directs. In a greased casserole, spread dressing. Drizzle with butter. In a bowl, combine chicken, celery, peppers, onion and pimento; mix well. Spread this over the stuffing. In a pan, combine flour, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Gradually stir in 1 1/2 cups bouillon mixture. Cook until mixture thickens, stirring often. In a cup, combine eggs and remaining bouillon mixture. Add to flour. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour mixture over casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Drain mushrooms. Put in pan. Add soup, sour cream and Tabasco sauce. Heat slowly for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve over chicken and stuffing.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla in blender, just a little.
Simmer milk.
Pour slowly in blender.
Bake in prepared pie shell for 10 minutes at 350°.
Then finish on 300°.

title: herb biscuits
directions: Stir together thoroughly all of the dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in center; add milk all at once.
Stir just until dough clings together.
Knead gently on lightly floured surface.
Roll out. Dip 2 1/2 inch biscuit-cutter in flour.
Cut dough straight down. Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: short breads
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light. Sift flour and cornstarch. Fold into creamed mixture. Roll out dough and form into shapes. Bake at 225° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle with granulated sugar if desired.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix and place in refrigerator for a while, then roll and cut. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add tomatoes, salt, soup and pepper. Simmer while cooking noodles.
Add cooked, drained noodles and half of cheese to meat mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with remainder of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: frozen cherry-pineapple salad
directions: Mix well and freeze in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: purple salad
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Combine thoroughly with sugar.
Drain pineapple and cherries well, then add to cheese and sugar mixture.
Add chopped nuts and Cool Whip. Chill in refrigerator.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; spoon into prepared crust.
Cover with top crust and crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: sweet corn cake
directions: Using electric mixer, cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt; beat just until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: cindy's cake
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients above for 8 minutes.
Combine chocolate bar and chocolate chips; add half to cake; mix.
Put in lightly greased Bundt pan.
Put remaining chocolate mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let set in pan 15 minutes to cool, then flip over on to plate to finish cooling.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: apple pie
directions: Put grated apples into pie shell.
Combine and cream the remaining ingredients.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake until firm.

title: crescent sesame swirls
directions: Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal (this prevents separation during baking). Place ham slices on rectangles.
Spread ham slices with mustard. Sprinkle with cheese.
Starting at shorter side, tightly roll up each rectangle, pressing edges to seal.
Coat rolls with sesame seeds.
Cut each roll into 5 slices, forming 20 slices.
Place cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup salt and water until it forms a ball in cold water.
Beat egg whites until it forms a peak.
Pour very slowly over beaten egg white.
Beat until mixture begins to part. Add nuts and vanilla and keep beating.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift cocoa, flour and sugar into pan and make sure it is well mixed.
Add the milk and egg yolks.
Set whites aside for the meringue.
Cook all ingredients in a pan on medium heat.
Stir often until thick.
Add a lump of butter and the vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake in 350° oven until meringue browns.

title: good neighbor cake
directions: Mix the first five ingredients well.
Add the remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and artichokes
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer chicken to a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, reserving drippings in skillet.
Add remaining 1/4 cup butter; cook over medium-high heat until butter melts; add mushrooms and saute until tender.
Remove mushrooms from skillet, reserving dripping in skillet.
Place mushrooms and artichoke hearts on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with tarragon.
Add flour to drippings in skillet, stirring until smooth.
Cook over low heat 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in sherry.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
Yields 8 servings.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put 1 tablespoon plus
teaspoons dill seed and 1 clove garlic in bottom
of
clean
jars.
Pack
the
jars
with cucumbers to fill.
Put 1 clove garlic on top.
Bring to a boil salt, vinegar and water.
Fill jars with hot liquid and seal.

title: marshmallow balls
directions: Melt butter over medium heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted; blend in dry gelatin.
Pour over corn and mix well. Butter hands and shape into balls.

title: key lime pie
directions: Place crumbs on flat microwavable plate and microwave approximately 2 minutes.
Set crumbs aside to cool.
Blend all other ingredients in blender until smooth.
Taste to see if lime or lemon extract is fine to taste.
In a parfait glass, alternate bread crumbs and pudding.
Serves 2.

title: stuffed beef rolls
directions: Trim fat from steak and pound steak slightly.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and scant amount of garlic powder.
Prepare 2 cups stuffing (from mix).
Cool.
Spread stuffing on steak; roll up and tie with string every 3 to 4-inches.
Brown 1 sliced onion in the drippings; add 1 cup water.
Simmer, then thicken.
Pour over beef rolls.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good served with mashed potatoes and a green salad.

title: cherry nut brownies
directions: Make brownies according to directions on box.
Add chocolate morsels, walnuts and cherries.
Bake for the shortest time allowed on brownie mix directions.
Cool approximately 3 to 4 hours.

title: gooseberry chutney
directions: Remove stems from berries.
Chop raisins and onions.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour into hot jars.
Seal at once.

title: killer chocolate sundae sauce(good for using up 10 pounds chocolate bars)
directions: Break chocolate into chunks in bowl and add milk to 1/4 cover chocolate. Microwave 1 minute. Stir vigorously until smooth. May need to add more milk if too thick.
Pour over ice cream and indulge.

title: old-fashioned apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In small bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon, flour and salt; mix well.
Add to apples in large bowl, tossing lightly to cover all.
Pour into unbaked pie shell, mounding high in center.
Dot with butter.
Add top of pie shell; cut 4 slits in top. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Stir the first 6 ingredients good.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cream the remaining ingredients good and have ready when the cake comes out of the oven.
Put on cake while hot.

title: pineapple chutney
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients except pineapple and raisins, over medium heat.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, with long, sharp knife, cut off crown and stem end of pineapple.
Stand pineapple upright.
Cut downward from top to remove rind; cut out eyes. Chop flesh into very small pieces.
Add pineapple and raisins to saucepan mixture.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Let cool; cover and refrigerate.
Makes about 1 pint.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Put in container and add enough water to make one gallon. (May need to add more sugar.)
Chill.
Put into punch bowl and add chilled ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Mix hot water, jello and marshmallows.	Cool and add Seven-Up and pineapple.
Let set.
Beat egg, butter, sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Cook until thick.
Cool.	Mix softened cream cheese with Cool Whip.
Fold in cooked mixture.
Spread on jello and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer.
Put soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Put cheese on top; bake until done.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Mix in a heavy 2-quart saucepan the sugar, milk, marshmallows or Creme, butter and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil (mixture will be bubbling all over top).
Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat.
Stir in until completely melted the chocolate chips.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Spread in a buttered 8-inch square pan; cool before cutting.

title: veggie squares
directions: Flatten dough on large cookie sheet with sides.
Pinch together any seams.
Bake crust 7 minutes at 375°; cool.
Mix together the cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise.
Spread on top of baked dough.
Top with vegetable mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or for several hours.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Pour scalded milk over salt and sugar.
Mix water and yeast; set aside.
When milk is lukewarm, add yeast, shortening, eggs and 4 cups flour.
Continue adding flour until dough is soft and not sticky (usually 4 cups).
Set aside in warm place, covered, until doubled.
Knead dough.
Roll out in circle.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up.
Pinch ends in.
Cut in pinwheels, desired width.
Rise 1/2 to 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until very light brown (do not overbake).
When cooled, frost.

title: roast chicken
directions: Put chicken in roasting pan.
Cover with melted butter. Sprinkle on garlic salt, salt, pepper, paprika and Italian seasoning.
Smother with soy sauce.
Put about 2 cups of water in bottom of roaster.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour in a well greased 9 by 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: octopus salad
directions: Boil the octopuses.
Let them cool and dice.
Add the minced onion and olive oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: stir fried veggies #1
directions: In a wok or large skillet, heat oil. Add all of the vegetables and stir fry over high heat, coating them with oil. Pour in the stock and soy sauce and stir until al dente, about 2 minutes more. Season with salt and pepper to taste, keeping in mind that soy sauce is also salty. Serve immediately. Makes 2 servings.

title: gator dip
directions: Combine sour cream with mashed avocado.
Add onion, dill, salt and pepper.
Combine and chill.
Also good as a dressing on tomatoes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients (except nuts) in bowl.
Cut in butter. Add remainder of ingredients and pour into a loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.
Remove from pan and wrap well at once in wax paper.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Pour mixture over crackers in large Tupperware or plastic bag. Turn and mix frequently.

title: hot artichoke hors d'oeuvre
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Lightly grease a 1 1/2-quart ovenproof bowl or Corning Ware dish with butter, margarine or use cooking spray.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese and garlic powder.
Fold in chopped artichoke hearts.
Cover top of mixture with crumbs. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve with party bread rounds.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt, mustard and mayo with mixer. Brown sausage and onion; drain well.
Layer sausage in a 9 x 9-inch greased dish with crumbled toast.
Cover with cheese, then pour egg mixture. Refrigerate overnight, then bake the next day at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: First Layer:
9 slices bread with crusts cut off.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: No peeping under any circumstances, as this cake will fall.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese.
Add beef, olives, onions and Accent.
Add everything.
Form in round ball.
Can roll in nuts.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: crisp molasses cookies
directions: Heat shortening and molasses in a saucepan until shortening is melted.
Stir constantly.
Slowly pour this mixture over the eggs. Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Roll to 1/16-inch thickness on a floured board or pastry cloth and cut with a 2-inch cookie cutter.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Dough may be frozen after sliced thin before baking.
Yield:
10 dozen.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Bake at 325° until done.
Take a fork and stick cake so icing can go through.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Pour over warm cake.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter in soup pot until tender. Add vegetables, water, bouillon and seasoning.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat and mash vegetables with potato masher.
Stir in milk and cheese. Simmer, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.

title: finger paints
directions: Combine cornstarch and 3/4 cup cold water in saucepan.
Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Stir hot water into cornstarch mixture.
Cook until clear, remove from heat.
Blend in softened gelatin.
Stir in soap until mixture is thoroughly dissolved. Cool.
Divide into jars.
Add different color dye to each jar.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir pecans in mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let cool.
Serves 8. Makes 2 pies.

title: morning casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain and place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix eggs and milk.
Then add mustard, salt, cheese and bread (diced).
Pour over sausage mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot sauce
directions: Place peppers, onions and vinegar in large pot.
Cook over medium heat until peppers and onions are soft (30 minutes). Remove solids and pulse in blender.
Add liquid and stir to blend thoroughly.
Season with salt to taste and store in covered jars or bottles.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in tightly covered container.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add other ingredients and simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: plains, georgia cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, nutmeg, oil, flavorings and water until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in nuts and peanut butter chips.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, vanilla, salt, oil, baking powder, and eggs.
Leave a little lumpy.
Add boiling water.
Mix up really well.
Then add baking soda.
Mix.
Bake at 350°F for 20 min.

title: spinach quiche(2 crust pie)
directions: Mix onion/sausage/spinach into the eggs, 1/2 c. ricotta cheese and 3 c. to 4 c. of shredded cheese (half mozzarella and half cheddar).
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350 degrees.
Makes 2.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumber and onion slices in large bowl.
Layer with salt; cover with ice cubes.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours; drain and rinse.
Place remaining ingredients in large pot; bring to a boil. Add drained cucumbers and onions.
Process 10 minutes in hot water canning bath.

title: vanilla crum cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Beat thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 275°. Test for doneness with a straw.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in 2 pie shells and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: In bowl, cut margarine into flour until mixture is crumbly. Stir in enough water until mixture forms a ball.
Set aside 1/4 of dough; roll remaining dough into an 11-inch circle.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate; trim and smooth edges.
Roll out reserved dough; cut into 1-inch leaves, attach to edge of crust using egg substitute.
In bowl beat remaining egg substitute, pumpkin, brown sugar and spice until blended.
Gradually mix in milk.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 10 servings, 204 calories; 6 grams fat each.

title: tomato-meat sauce (spaghetti sauce)
directions: Chop onion.
Cook in the fat or oil in a frypan until tender and lightly browned.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Cook over low heat for about 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Add a little water during cooking, if needed.
Makes 2 servings, about 1/2 cup each.

title: knickerbocker rolls
directions: In a large warm bowl, dissolve the yeast in the warm water. Let stand until bubbly, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir together several cups of the flour with the sugar and salt until well mixed. Add flour mixture to yeast mixture along with the slightly beaten eggs, oil and warm milk.
Beat to blend well.
Gradually stir in more flour.
Most home electric mixers will not be able to handle 10 cups of flour.
This means you'll have to use your hands and muscle power to mix in the flour and knead the dough.
The 10 cups is an approximate figure.
It may take slightly more or less flour to get a nice, soft dough.
Try not to add too much flour.
Cover bowl and let batter rise in a warm place until doubled, about 45 minutes.
This warm place needs to be about 85° to 90°.
Roll out dough and cut out.
The restaurant baker uses a small grapefruit juice can.
Put rolls on buttered cookie sheet and let rise again for another 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake in the preheated oven for 10 to 17 minutes, or until rolls are lightly browned.
Makes 100 + rolls, just lightly brown and pop them in the freezer.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter until tender; add mushrooms and juice, soy sauce, salt and pepper.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; tear into small pieces.
Combine chicken, sour cream, poppy seeds, soups and crackers, saving some of the crackers for the top of casserole.
Mix well pour into baking dish; sprinkle reserved crackers over top and put pats of butter on crackers.
Bake in 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with salad.

title: chicken wraps
directions: Place olive oil in a skillet and heat, add chicken and onion and cook until chicken is done and onions are tender. Remove from heat. Place chicken and onion mixture in a large bowl and add taco seasoning, sour cream, cheese, tomatoes, avocado and lettuce and stir well. Place mixture in the center of each tortilla and roll up. Slice in half and serve.

title: easy chicken cordon bleu
directions: Lay chicken breasts flat on surface.
Place a piece of ham, then a piece of cheese on chicken.
Start rolling chicken up.
You may place a toothpick in chicken to hold but leave up so it can be removed before serving.
Place chicken in dish and cover with undiluted soup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Cut dill pickles in slices as thick as a silver dollar.
Mix together remaining ingredients to form a batter.
Dip the pickle slices in the batter and quickly fry in grease at 375° until they float to the top, about 4 minutes.

title: apple cheese casserole(from gift horse restaurant, foley, al)
directions: Simmer apples in boiling water until tender.
Remove from water and place a layer in buttered casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Repeat layering until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes (delicious).

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 4 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Layer potatoes and other ingredients.
Heat in 350° oven until all melted together.
Can add salt and pepper to taste.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, put your onion, chopped fine, your cooking oil, Worcestershire sauce, your catsup, pepper, salt and brown sugar.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Have your pork or beef in a baking pan.
Pour sauce on meat.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Simmer onions in a small amount of water until soft.
Add chicken pieces and dressing.
Cook over medium high heat until brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Browning should take about 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms and stewed tomatoes.
Turn heat down to medium.
Simmer until juice boils down and sauce forms a rich coating over all ingredients.
Serve over white rice or with a side of baked potato.
Enjoy!

title: mom's sweet potato pone
directions: Add molasses, well beaten eggs, milk, butter and ginger (or orange rind) to grated potatoes.
Mix well and pour into well-greased skillet or baking pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon over top when half done.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Serve with slices of fruit.

title: sad cake
directions: Combine sugar and Bisquick.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix until creamy.
Add oil and stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased Sheet cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cake will be moist.

title: golden harvest muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line muffin cups with paper liners. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In 4-quart bowl, combine all-purpose and wheat flours, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Add apples, carrots, coconut, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Add oil, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Stir just until moistened.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
May freeze in freezer bags up to 1 month.

title: orange jello ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir 2 cups boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured juice/water (1 cup).
Refrigerate
about 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened (like unbeaten egg whites).
Stir in Cool Whip topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold.
Makes 10 servings.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Cook, covered in boiling water until tender.
Drain; reserve 2/3 cup cooking water.
Mash potatoes. Set aside.
(You should have 2 cups.)
Combine flour, soda and spices in an extra-large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, oil, sugar, sweet potatoes and reserved cooking water in another mixing bowl.
Stir into flour mixture until well combined.
Stir in pecans and raisins.
Divide mixture evenly among three greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch or 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch pans.

title: randy's almost famous hush puppies
directions: Add water to make batter have the consistency of cake batter. Deep fry over medium heat until golden brown.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Melt margarine and add all ingredients but chicken.
Bring to a boil, then simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Marinate chicken in 1/2 to 3/4 of barbecue sauce for a minimum of 24 hours. Grill over low-medium heat using reserved sauce for basting.

title: ritzy chicken casserole
directions: Crumble one sleeve of crackers in the bottom of a 2 1/2 qt. casserole dish.

Drizzle 1/2 of the melted margarine over the crackers. Mix crackers with soup, sour cream and broth. Pour over crackers. Crush the remaining sleeve of crackers and pour over the chicken mixture, drizzle the remaining margarine over the crackers.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Heat caramels and margarine in double boiler, stirring until blended. Combine sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Gradually add caramel mixture. Mix well and add pecans.
Pour into unbaked shell. Bake 40 minutes at 350°. (I place my pecans the way I want them.)

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add to beaten eggs and pineapple.
Pour mixture into buttered casserole.
Melt butter or margarine in frying pan.
Cut bread slices in small squares.
Stir in hot butter until brown.
Put on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake one-half to three-quarters of an hour in moderate oven.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken and save broth.
Saute onion and peppers in butter.
Mix with soups and tomatoes.
Dip tortillas in chicken broth and cover 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of chicken, soup mixture and cheese, then repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle top with chili and garlic powder.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: almond apple crisp
directions: Mix water, almond extract and apples.
Place in 9-inch baking dish.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain and wash peas; add onions and garlic.
Stir and add oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Marinate overnight.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Cut up strawberries and mix in the glaze.
Set aside.
Pinch up cake in the bottom of bowl.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, powdered sugar and condensed milk.
Pour over cake.
Pour strawberry mixture over this.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: western beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in butter.
Drain excess grease.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Garnish with bacon bits.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grandma olson's potato sausage
directions: Grind and mix well.
Stuff into beef casings.
(Ingredients can be purchased at Viaus Market or Adams Grocery.)

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 to 4 hours.
Garnish with fruit of your choice (optional).

title: glaze
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Can be use for cakes.

title: sugarless oatmeal cookies(diabetic)
directions: Combine all ingredients, beating well.
Let stand 5 minutes so that oats will absorb moisture.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute on cookie sheets; transfer to wire racks to cool completely.
Yield: 2 1/2 dozen cookies.
Each serving amount:
1 cookie.
Exchanges:
1/2 starch.

title: jonnie sausage casserole
directions: Put 1 package of rolls in bottom of 2-quart casserole, mix drained cooked sausage, cheese and egg over rolls.
Cover with second package of crescent rolls, dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package, no salt.
Combine broccoli, soup, milk, butter and dry onion soup mix in a large skillet. Bring mixture to a boil over a medium heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in rice.

title: hershey's kiss cookies
directions: Combine the flour, soda and salt.
Cream the shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add the egg and vanilla. Mix together.
Form into small balls and roll in white sugar. Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a "Kiss" in the middle of each cookie.
Return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix in large bowl wax beans, kidney beans, green beans, onions and garlic.
Heat sugar, vinegar and oil in saucepan until sugar dissolves.
Cool slightly and add oregano, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly and chill overnight.
Remove garlic before serving.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15x10x1 inch baking pan with no stick cooking spray.
Stir together the Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs and herbs and spices.
Dip chicken in margarine, then coat with the Parmesan cheese mixture.
Place in prepared pan and bake 20-25 minutes, or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: poor man's turkey
directions: Brown meat and green pepper (do not season.)
Drain excess fat. Place in casserole dish.
Add soup, water and dressing.
Mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Line ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with crescent rolls.
Brown sausage and cover dough with sausage.
Sprinkle hash browns over sausage; next sprinkle cheese, then pour egg and mix mixture over cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes (can freeze before baking).

title: round french sourdough bread and dip
directions: Cut top off bread.
Remove center and cut into cubes.
Fill center of bread with mixture of mayonnaise, sour cream, onion, Beau Monde and ham or beef.
Dip pieces of bread into dip and place around outside of loaf.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix well.
Batter will be very stiff.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan, that has been lightly greased.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in the order listed.
Spread mayonnaise over peas.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Top with cheese and bacon bits.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Drain. Rinse with cold water.
Drain again; set aside.

title: fritters
directions: *Vegetable recommended is corn.

title: vegie bars
directions: On cookie sheet, unroll crescent rolls and smooth with fingers to cover bottom.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool 20 minutes.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients, adding pecans last.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer or until a silver knife inserted in center of filling comes out clean.

title: chicken a la tomato
directions: Pour olive oil in pan and heat.
Add garlic and onion and saute.
Add chicken and cook thoroughly (you can cover and let cook, just check it so it won't burn).
When the chicken is almost cooked, add the tomatoes, this makes the sauce.
Keep covered and simmer.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Using margarine, grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all of the ingredients together and place into the baking dish.
Place "dabs" of margarine or butter on top of casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Reheats well.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix applesauce and cinnamon together to form a stiff dough. Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Make a hole for the ribbon.
Carefully put on a rack to dry.
Let air dry for several days, turning occasionally.

title: nathan's favorite lasagne
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Mince garlic; brown lightly with crumbled beef in oil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Butter large casserole.
Cover bottom with layer of noodles.
Add sliced cheese, Ricotta, then meat mixture.
Repeat layers; top with Parmesan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Can be made day before and reheated, uncovered.
Good with green salad, mandarin oranges and French bread.

title: easy shrimp dish
directions: Cook shrimp in about one quart of boiling salted water. Remove shrimp when water boils for 5 minutes.
Clean shrimp.
Set aside and save shrimp water.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in margarine until onions are transparent.
Add mushrooms and cook one minute more.
Add shrimp water and heat.
Add dissolved cornstarch and cook just until thick and clear (about 1 minute). Add shrimp to hot mixture and serve over cooked rice.
Pass the soy sauce.

title: soft gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together, then add molasses and egg and stir.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cloves, ginger and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture and stir well.
Shape dough in small round balls; dip in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 8 minutes (10 minutes for harder cookies).

title: honey dijon drumsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine mustard, bouillon and honey. Coat drumsticks with mustard mixture.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Arrange in greased baking dish.
Drizzle margarine over drumsticks.
Bake 40 minutes or until chicken is tender. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: whole lemon custards
directions: With a sharp knife, cut yellow part of peel from lemon.
Put into a blender container.
Cut off and discard white part of peel. Coarsely chop lemon meat.
Discard any seeds.
Put in blender. To lemon, add eggs, sugar and butter.
Whirl until smoothly blended.
Pour lemon mixture evenly into four (6-ounce) custard cups or other ovenproof dishes.
Set into an 8-inch square pan. Pour 1/2 inch hot water into pan around cups.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until centers of custards are not longer liquidy when shaken.
Lift custards from water bath; let cool at least 15 minutes.
Refrigerate to chill for 2 to 8 hours.
Garnish with sliced strawberries.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Beat egg yolks well and add.
Add 1/2 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla in half the apples.
Add to mixture.
Mix the spices, nuts, fruits and raisins in all the flour.
Alternate with flour mixture and stiffly beaten egg whites. Add remaining applesauce with 1 teaspoon soda.
Put soda on top of applesauce and stir.
Add to other mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in slow (very) oven in greased and floured tube pan about 2 1/2 hours. Use 1 teaspoon cocoa for dark cake.

title: potato pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, spices and milk.
Add butter to mashed potatoes and blend with milk and egg mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes longer.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion in a little fat until brown.
Add meat and seasoning.
Brown.
Add tomato soup.
Pour this mixture into a baking dish.
Add drained peas on top, then mashed potatoes and season them.
Spoon in mounds over peas and meat.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix together pudding and milk.
Combine the two separate mixtures and then add Cool Whip.

title: spinach squares(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs; add and mix all together the remaining ingredients.
Put in pan and spread evenly.
Sprinkle seasoned salt on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Peel and cube.
Add onions, green pepper, Velveeta cheese (cubed), pimientos, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together.
Pour over top enough milk to moisten, about 1/2 cup.
Marinate overnight.
Top with crushed corn flakes. Drizzle 1 stick of melted oleo over top.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine liquid ingredients in a large bowl.
Add dry mixture of flour, cream of tartar and salt.
Blend well and chill dough overnight.
Roll into small balls and roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes. Cool on rack.
Makes 48 to 60 cookies.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Beat well and pour over baked crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Then combine 1/2 cup chopped pecans, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 2 Tbsp. oleo.
Sprinkle over pumpkin filling:
return to oven and bake for 20 minutes more or until filling sets.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender, 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid, and set veggies aside.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Grease griddle and heat. For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup batter.
Cook until bubbly. Flip, cook until golden.
Serve with applesauce.
Makes 10 to 12.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl. Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, chocolate chips and nuts. Place tablespoons of cookie dough on baking sheet.
Bake at 350, until light brown in color.
Do not overbake.

title: spaghetti chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove; set aside.
Cook spaghetti in broth from chicken.
While spaghetti is cooking in separate pan, saute onion in butter with celery.
When that's done, add soups, tomatoes and chicken to saute mixture.
Put spaghetti in a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Add soup mixture.
Top with cheese.
Heat oven to 350° until cheese melts.
Taste even better left over.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Bake cake as package directs for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool well.
Cut cake into 1-inch squares.
Layer ingredients in a clear punch bowl in order given.
Repeat.
Top with cherries.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix with peach pie filling.
Let this set until ready to serve.
Add bananas and strawberries and sugar when ready to serve.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: fruity delight
directions: With mixer, mix sour cream, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Stir in fruit cocktail, pineapple and strawberry jello.
Mix well. Ready when mixed or can be chilled.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add vanilla, then eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour and 7-UP.
Pour in tube pan and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan melt butter. Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: sandy's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except for the cheese.
Mix well and shape into a pond, reserving 1/3 of the mixture.
Put meat loaf on covered cookie sheet.
Place cheese in the center of the pond. Cover with remaining meat loaf mixture.
Cover meat loaf with catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour approximately.

title: long john silver mock fish batter
directions: Mix together.
Dip fish in to coat then fry.

title: baked pork ribs
directions: Skin the inside skin from the ribs, stick knife under it and peel.
Rub ribs with brown sugar.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° oven. Put barbecue sauce on the last 15 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add bread and beat at high speed until well blended.
Add skim milk powder, baking powder, lemon rind and sweetener, mixing a minute longer.
Gently fold in berries.
Pour mixture into 8 cupcake tins that have been coated with Pam spray. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicago style italian beef sandwiches(8 sandwiches)
directions: Place meat in 5-quart (I prefer cast-iron) Dutch oven and completely cover with beer.
Tie allspice, peppercorns and bay leaves in a cloth bag (I use cheesecloth) and add to the kettle. Add salt, marjoram and half of the onion.
Simmer for 2 hours in covered pot.
Dice all vegetables and add to kettle.
Cover and simmer for approximately 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Remove the cloth bag and serve.
Serve with hearty wheat rolls. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Then sprinkle the ingredients over it in layers.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Mix other ingredients and heat. Pour into greased casserole.
Top with biscuit topping.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until biscuit top is done.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix as you would any pound cake.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: crunchy mallow candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat. Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into a 9-inch greased pan (butter flavored Pam is good).
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: sparklin emerald punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add cold water, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Before serving add chilled ginger ale, pour carefully to avoid excess foam.

title: grandma goodfellow's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thinly.
Add onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt.
Cover with cracked ice; mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients in large kettle.
Add cucumber mixture; bring just to a boil.
Seal in hot jars.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 8 pints.

title: chicken in the garden
directions: Place in large baking dish enough chicken, sliced potatoes (not thin slices), peeled carrots and sliced onion to cover dish. Add approximately 3/4 soup can of water with soup.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Add the butter or margarine in 1 tablespoon slices.
Cover with foil and bake for approximately 1 hour at 400°.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Mix salsa and cream cheese and put in serving dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on one half and olives on the other half.
Serve with taco chips.

title: aunt lucy's okra
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil or grease and cook until light golden.
Drain on paper towels before serving.

title: nicole's black bean relish
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion, celery, carrot, garlic and jalapeno peppers in butter or margarine until onion is tender. Stir in black beans, ham, cilantro or parsley and salt.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until desired consistency.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: honey cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift other ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Chill.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut.
Put on lightly greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
These come out soft.

title: out-of-bounds candy bars
directions: Combine 1/4 cup (60 ml) of the coconut, the milk, the gelatin and cornstarch in blender; blend until smooth.
Pour into small saucepan; cook and stir over medium heat until slightly thickened. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and remaining coconut.
Form into 8 bars.
Allow to firm and cool completely and dip in chocolate.

title: easy macaroni and cheese for two
directions: Cook macaroni for 15 minutes; drain.
Run water over; drain. Put back into pan.
Add margarine, cheese, milk, salt and pepper. Cook until it thickens.

title: spinach salad with sweet and sour dressing
directions: Wash and dry spinach; remove stems.
Mix all ingredients except egg and bacon in a shaker.
Sprinkle over spinach.
Top with egg, bacon and sesame seed.

title: bread in a jar
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, bananas or your flavor and water.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add mixtures together and mix well. Add nuts. Pour mixture into jars filling half full. Place jars on cookie sheet in oven and bake at 325°
for 45 minutes.
When bread is done remove jars one at a time and whip off edges and seal with lids tightly.
The heat will seal the jars and the bread will keep for 1 year.
If you like, you can use self rising flour and leave out baking powder, soda, and salt.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook the broccoli and onions together.
Do not drain.
Add soup, broth and milk.
Simmer until hot.
Stir in cheese until melted.

title: moist coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, egg yolks and sugar.
Add milk and sifted dry ingredients, then beaten egg whites.
Pour into oblong cake pan and sprinkle with topping.

title: molasses crisp cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses and then add all other dry ingredients.
Chill overnight, or at least a couple of hours.
Make into balls.
Dip one side into sugar and press out with a fork on a cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix together cheese and sausage.
To this, add biscuit dough. Divide the dry biscuit mix into 3 equal parts, adding each part separately.
The mixture will be stiff and should be kneaded several times.
The cheese and sausage will hold the dough together.
Set aside.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, celery, beef, onions and tomatoes in greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Garnish with green pepper rings.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Boil 1 cup water with cornstarch until clear; add jello. Stir until dissolved and add 1 cup cold water. Pour mixture over strawberries that have been placed in the pie shell. Chill and top with whipped topping (I use Cool Whip).

title: madonna salad
directions: Cook together apricot Jell-O, sugar and pineapple until it boils.
Let
cool.	Mix cream cheese and baby food together with mixer.
Stir
into	Jell-O	mixture.
Stir	in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut into squares. Serve warm with sweetened whipped cream.

title: crock pot cube steaks
directions: Brown cube steaks in olive oil.
Place steaks in crock pot. Add soup with water as directed on can.
Add soup mix; stir to combine.

title: ham salad
directions: Grind ham, eggs and pickle relish.
Mix together Miracle Whip, vinegar, sugar and milk and pour over ham mixture.
Mix together.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Beat eggs and cream with sugar and margarine.
Add vanilla. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and let set 1 hour before serving.

title: old fashioned spicy chili
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring to crumble meat, until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off pan drippings.
Stir in chili powder, flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well (mixture will be very thick).
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes over low heat.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pecan or peanut brittle
directions: Bring to a good boil.
Add broken up pecans.
Cook about 7 minutes or until it turns a caramel color.
Take off stove.
Add margarine.
Take off stove and add soda.
Stir very fast and mix well.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Spread over sheet.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Fully cook sausage; drain.
Combine sausage, onion, cheese, flour and parsley flakes.
Mix well.
Spread in unbaked pie shell. Beat together eggs and evaporated milk; pour over sausage mixture.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is set.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and bell pepper until tender, drain well. Mash and add margarine and cheese or cheese soup, stir until cheese melts.
Mix milk and eggs.
Add to squash.
Mix well, then add crushed saltines.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: cheesy fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle both sides with salt and allow to sit 30 minutes.
Rinse eggplant slices and pat dry.
Combine bread crumbs and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Place slice of cheese between 2 slices of eggplant.
Trim cheese to fit.
Dip eggplant-cheese sandwich in egg and dredge in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli separately. Drain broccoli. Add the other ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Serves 8 to 10.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, and whipped topping.
Pour in pie crust.
Top with with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.
Serve chilled.

title: layered dessert
directions: Spread everything into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan in order given. Drain pineapple juice to pour on top of dry cake mix with melted margarine.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.
You can top with Cool Whip.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes; peel and slice.
Arrange in layers in a greased casserole, sprinkling each layer with brown sugar, salt and bits of butter.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes six servings.

title: quick and lite quiche lorraine
directions: Combine onion and turkey bacon in medium skillet, heated with olive oil.
Cook 10 minutes over medium-high heat.
Thaw pie crust and bake in a 375° preheated oven for 5 minutes.
Spread onion mixture in pie crust.
Top onion mixture with cheese and set aside.

title: easy chicken
directions: Marinate chicken for 1 hour and then grill or bake in the oven.

title: deviled bluefish cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into clam shells.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and place under broiler until slightly browned.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Cut rolls in halves; drop around in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle mixture of butterscotch pudding, brown sugar and cinnamon over dough.
Sprinkle pecans on top; pour melted butter on next.
Cover with foil and towel.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(I bake even longer.)

title: make ahead french toast with strawberry sauce
directions: Arrange half of challah bread in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with cheese pieces and top with remaining bread. Whisk together eggs and next 3 ingredients. Pour over bread mixture; cover and chill 8 hours. Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes. Uncover and bake 20 more minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in loaf pan and shape. Garnish with catsup and olives.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: brown bread
directions: Sift flour, cornmeal, soda and salt in large mixing bowl. Measure in cold water.
Add molasses; mix thoroughly.
Beat with wire whisk to get the flour lumps out.
Pour into two greased 1-pound coffee cans.
Set in kettle of water; steam for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: amaretto cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup blanched almonds and 1/3 cup sugar in food processor.
Add the butter and process thoroughly. Press mixture into bottom and up halfway on sides of 8 1/2-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimiento, pepper and 1/2 cup of the crumbs.

title: caramel cereal bars
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, mix cereals and peanuts.
In medium bowl, microwave caramels and water on Medium for 3 to 5 minutes until caramels are melted, stirring every 2 minutes.
Pour over cereal and mix thoroughly.
Spray hands and press into pan. Let stand for 1 hour.

title: potato salad from grandma noyes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on.
Cool, peel and cut into bite size pieces.
Place in large bowl.
Cook and peel eggs.
Chop 6 eggs, using egg slicer 2 ways.
Add to bowl.
Slice 2 eggs, using egg slicer 1 way and set aside for garnish.
Finely chop celery stalks and add to bowl.
Spoon 3/4 jar of Miracle Whip into bowl and mix until all potatoes are well covered.
Add salt and pepper to taste and mix in.
Garnish top with reserved egg slices and lightly sprinkle with paprika.
Chill and serve.
(This salad is best served chilled, not ice cold.)
Serves 15 to 18.

title: berniece's apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar in bowl; let stand for 1 hour.
Beat eggs with oil and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla in large bowl.
Sift in mixture of flour, soda, salt and spices; mix well.
Add apples and nuts and mix well.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup and can of cream; mix cornbread stuffing with chicken broth.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with chicken.
Spread stuffing on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: zucchini and onions with mozzarella
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients except tomato and cheese.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is crisp-tender (7 to 10 minutes).
Add tomato wedges.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and let stand 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: orange and grape tortellini salad
