directions: Cook and cool tortellini. Combine all other ingredients and toss in bowl.

title: mom's beef barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger with garlic and onion.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: sausage puff
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix with softened cream cheese. Unroll crescent rolls into rectangles.
Put mixture down middle of dough and roll back up.
Makes 8 rolls.
Refrigerate until firm. Slice into 1-inch slices.

title: vegetable stuffed bundles
directions: Arrange 1/6 of the vegetables on each cube steak. Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Over medium heat, in hot oil, brown on all sides.
Remove skillet from heat.
Remove beef rolls.
Add soup and water. Stir well, but gently. Add beef rolls.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin and water according to package directions.
Add strawberries and pineapple, mixing well.
Put half of mixture in dish and refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream over chilled gelatin, then put remaining gelatin mixture on top.
Refrigerate until set.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt and spices.
Blend Wesson oil and sugar.
Add eggs and prunes; beat until light and fluffy. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 x 13 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ham delicious
directions: Mix milk with dry ingredients until smooth and pour over ham arranged in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until tender.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, margarine, shortening and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in flour, tartar, soda and salt. Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll balls in mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: blintz loaf
directions: Melt butter and blend with cottage cheese in a bowl with mixer until smooth.
Slowly add Bisquick and sugar.
Blend well. Add eggs one at at time.
Pour mixture into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve with jam and/or sour cream.

title: white velvet pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add 1 egg at a time; blend well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: black bean salad
directions: Soak beans overnight; cook until just tender.
Drain and cool. Add corn, scallions, celery, bell pepper, relish and cumin. Stir to mix thoroughly.
Add vinegar, oil and salt and pepper; mix in.
Add cheese last, mixing carefully to avoid breaking up cubes. Makes 6 servings of about 1 cup each.

title: cabbage soup(low calorie)
directions: Cook all ingredients together.
Let simmer until tender (approximately 20 minutes).

title: oatmeal patties
directions: Mix together.
Form patties by dropping heaping tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Makes 6 patties.
Make gravy.
Bake 30 minutes in gravy.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add egg. Sift dry ingredients together. Combine molasses and hot water. Combine all ingredients and mix together. Place into 10-inch square or 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and mix together.
Refrigerate for a few hours.
Great for a family gathering.

title: zucchini bread(with pineapple variation)
directions: Beat together oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add zucchini. Add dry ingredients.
Optional:
Stir in pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans (or 1 large pan). Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dublin potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
Peel and cube.
While still warm, add vinegar, celery seed and mustard.
Sprinkle on 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt and lightly toss.
Chill potato mixture.
Add cabbage, pickle, corned beef and green onion to potato mixture.
Make a dressing of mayonnaise and milk; add to potato mixture.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan with butter.
Place a layer of graham crackers on bottom of pan.
Prepare pudding with milk and then blend in Cool Whip; mix well.
Pour half of mixture on graham crackers.
Place
a second layer of crackers on pudding.
Cover this with remaining pudding.
Add a third layer of crackers.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top of last layer of crackers. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pecan drops
directions: Add to beaten egg, folding in carefully, the other ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet lined with waxed or parchment paper. Bake at 250° for 30 min or until dry. Watch carefully to avoid burning.

title: malawach
directions: Mix flour, water and salt until dough becomes soft.
Add more flour if dough is sticky.
Cut dough into two sections.
Knead and roll each section into a 20 x 20-inch sheet.
Spread margarine on the sheets.
Fold each sheet like an envelope with ends meeting at center.
Repeat folding process to get two layers of folds.
Cover with a paper towel.
Let sit for 1/2 hour.
Cut each sheet into 10 parts.
Form each piece of dough to the shape of your frying pan and fry until golden brown on both sides.
Serve with tomato sauce or sour cream.

title: sunny day punch
directions: Combine punch and juices.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: cheesecake appetizer
directions: Mix with mixer.
Put one vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake paper.
Pour topping on each.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. May add a cherry or blueberry or strawberry on top when it is cool.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Beat eggs well.
Gradually beat in remaining ingredients except nuts.
Fold in last.
Grease 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: vi's cream puffs
directions: Put this in frypan
and
when
butter
is
melted,
add flour. Cook until flour, butter and water have formed a ball. Place in a dish and add 1 egg at a time until 4 eggs have been beaten into the mixture.
Drop from spoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake
in hot oven at 425° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 minutes longer.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel the eggplant. Cut into 1/2-inch slices. Dip in egg and bread crumbs.
Brown both sides.
Place 1/2 in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Add rest of the eggplant.
Bring sauce to a boil and pour over eggplant.
Add rest of cheese.
Cover casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Add enough whole milk to fill container to 2/3 full.
You may add 2 cups of any kind of crushed fruit (peaches, strawberries, pineapple or cherries).

title: strawberry banana cream pie
directions: Prepare Jell-O with only 2 cups boiling water; stir to dissolve Jell-O and stir in frozen berries.
Set in fridge and stir frequently until Jell-O gets thick, not set, about 20 minutes.
Pour 1/4 mixture in crust, slice bananas over jello, spread 1/4 Jell-O over that and set in fridge.
Mix pudding with 1 cup milk for thickness.
Spread on pie.
Pour 1/4 Jell-O on pudding.
Slice other banana on that.
Spread remaining Jell-O over top.
Refrigerate until solidly set.
Spoon Cool Whip on top in 8 serving sections and a bigger spoonful in middle.
Place strawberry on each Cool Whip dollop.

title: jelly roll
directions: Stir egg yolks lightly; add sugar.
Stir until creamy.
Add ice water and blend.
Sift flour and baking powder several times. Sift into bowl, stirring.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites with salt.
Bake in a long, shallow pan at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on damp cloth and spread with jelly.
Roll up while warm. When cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine hot water, salt, shortening and sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast to lukewarm water and let soften, the add to cooled mixture.
Add beaten egg, half of the flour and beat well. Stir in more flour, enough to make dough easy to handle.
Grease top of dough, cover with wax paper and a dish towel held by rubber bands.
Store in refrigerator.

title: flounder with tomatoes and sweet garlic sauce
directions: Combine the garlic and 2 cups water in a small saucepan.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Drain garlic; cool in ice water, then drain again. Heat 1/2 cup of the olive oil in a skillet over high heat.
Add the onions and tomatoes; saute until golden, about 5 minutes, stirring. Add garlic, thyme, tarragon and salt and pepper to taste; simmer for 8 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown together first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, except chili beans and cracker crumbs and simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Remove garlic buds and pepper before serving.
Add beans and cracker crumbs.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and eggs.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Pour into angel food cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scroodle salad
directions: Cook the celery seed, sugar, mustard, flour, vinegar, salt and margarine until bubbles and thickens.
(Will be a little thicker than water.)
Pour over the first 7 ingredients and let stand overnight.

title: glorified ginger cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and flour together and take out 1/2 cup crumbs for top of cake.
Make a hole in center.
Mix and add the egg, molasses, sour milk and soda.
Mix all together and add crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: freezer corn
directions: Cut corn off husks.
Put in roasting pan.
Add butter and half and half.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Put in bowls and set bowls in ice.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: baked chicken broccoli & rice
directions: In 2 quart oblong baking dish, combine soup, water and rice. Arrange chicken over rice mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and pepper.

title: quick pecan breakfast ring
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar and milk in 2-cup glass measuring cup.
Melt and bring to a boil.
Sprinkle nuts in 8-cup plastic or microwavable tube pan.
Pour half of brown sugar mixture over nuts.
Arrange biscuits, overlapping slightly in dish.
Top with remaining brown sugar mixture.
Cook on level 7 for 8 minutes.
Turn one-quarter turn halfway through cooking time.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Invert onto serving platter.
Serve immediately.

title: monte cristo
directions: Mix together 1 egg, vanilla, milk, cinnamon and sugar.
Fry 2 eggs.
Butter 4 slices bread on 1 side.
Place 1 egg and meat of choice and cheese between bread slices making 2 sandwiches.
Dip sandwiches in egg and milk mixture.
Grill in skillet on medium heat.
Great breakfast!

title: apple fritter
directions: Mix all ingredients except apples, Hi-Energy Vanilla Supplement and bread together thoroughly.
Tear bread into tiny pieces and soak in mixture.
Add apples (or other fruit).
Stir and drop by tablespoons into hot Teflon skillet with 1 teaspoon oil; cook until brown.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with vanilla supplement.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla. Beat mixture until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in grated zucchini.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Fold in nuts or raisins.
Bake 1 hour at 350°
in 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then remove.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine the milk, water, sugar, salt and butter and mix thoroughly in a 3-quart saucepan.
Heat to the boiling point over moderate heat.
Cook to 248° or firm ball, stirring constantly.
A full rolling boil should be maintained throughout.
Remove from heat.
Cool at room temperature without stirring until lukewarm (110°).
Add vanilla and beat until mixture snaps and keeps its shape.
Add 3/4 cup marshmallow cream and 1/3 cup chopped fruit and beat again until mixture loses its gloss and is very stiff.
Pour quickly into buttered pan and cut in squares.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in large non-stick skillet over medium heat. Stack tortillas, cut in half then crosswise making narrow strips. Fry half the tortilla strips, turning often, 5 minutes or until lightly browned & crisp. Remove from pan, place on paper towels to drain oil. Repeat with remaining strips.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, shortening, egg and milk like pie dough.
Spread in bottom of a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan. Spread rhubarb over dough.
Sprinkle over this strawberry jello. Mix together sugar, flour and oleo.
Sprinkle over top and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until done.
(Very good!)

title: cheddar ham chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, bring the water, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Do not drain.

title: fruity haystacks
directions: Melt the bark as directions on the package. Add all other ingredients together and dip out by spoonful on wax paper or foil.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix cornstarch into measured Pet milk.
In bowl, mix pineapple, butter, sugar, egg and Pet milk.
Stir in cracker crumbs and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until thick.

title: french dressing
directions: Makes almost a quart.

title: baked stew(serves 8)
directions: Place all ingredients in order given in roaster with tight fitting lid.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
No browning necessary. When done, the gravy will be thick and brown.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Drop cookies by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes on sheet before removing.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, egg yolks (beaten), sugar (1/2 cup), milk and butter in saucepan.
Cool and add vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust, then beat whites of eggs stiff with 3 tablespoons sugar and put on top of custard.
Crush some graham crackers and put on top of egg whites.
Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour.

title: caramelized onions in squash
directions: Cut squash lengthwise.
Remove seeds and strings.
Place cut side down in a shallow baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn squash, cut side up; bake 15 to 20 minutes more or until tender. While squash are baking, heat sugar over medium heat in heavy skillet until caramelized.
Add onions, butter and orange peel. Cook, stirring constantly, for 7 to 8 minutes until onions are tender and glazed.
Spoon mixture into squash and serve.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grate 2 tablespoons orange peel.
Peel oranges and separate in sections.
Remove seeds and membranes.
Put oranges, sugar and grated peel into blender.
Blend well.
Add cranberries; blend until all have been blended well!
Makes 4 cups.

title: pineapple pie
directions: In large bowl beat flour, margarine, eggs and sugar with mixer.
Add 1 can crushed pineapple, stir by hand.
Pour all ingredients into 2 unbaked pie shells 9 inch.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: ritz-baked chicken
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken, dip well in Egg Beaters (defrost Egg Beaters and use while very cold), then roll or press chicken breasts in the crushed Ritz crackers.
Place in baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
If you have cracker crumbs left, place on top of chicken.

title: easy yellow layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans. Mix dry ingredients. Fold in rest of ingredients.
Pour into pans. Bake about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dumpling dough
directions: Mix buttermilk, water and eggs.
Add enough flour to become biscuit-like mixture.
Work dough hard.
Roll dough paper thin. Cut in strips, about 1-inch thick.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1/2-quart casserole, stir sugar, syrup, pecans and salt, mixing well.
Microwave on High, 6 to 9 minutes until light brown. Add butter and vanilla and stir well.
Microwave on High, 1 to 2 minutes more.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour into a lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheesy asparagus or broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Add asparagus (cut into large pieces) or broccoli and cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Garnish with a sprinkling of Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Serves 6.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: Note:
Add yeast cake to 1/2 cup lukewarm water.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Set oven to 425°.
Melt butter.
Brush on chicken.
Roll chicken in instant potato flakes.
Shake on salt. Bake in oven at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Good topping for ribs, chicken, etc.

title: cherry pie
directions: Over medium heat mix first seven ingredients until thickened. Pour cherries into unbaked crust.
Add sauce.
Dot with margarine. Cover with top crust or lattice.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Preparation time: 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: This cheese cake is so good.
I have been making them since I was fifteen.
We brought this recipe with us from New York.
I have 5 sisters and every year for their birthdays all they wanted was a cheese cake, so I made a lot of cheese cakes over the years.

title: trail bologna
directions: Mix well; put into 2 rolls on wax paper.
Do not wrap the rolls.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Meat will turn dark.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Pat with paper towel and cool.

title: fruity coleslaw
directions: Combine 1/2 c. light mayonnaise, 20 oz. can crushed pineapple in juice, and 1 Tbsp. poppy seeds in a large bowl. Add grated apple, broccoli coleslaw, grapes, strawberries, and mandarin oranges to the dressing and stir until covered with dressing. Serve chilled.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream oleo, peanut butter, sugars and egg. Add dry ingredients. Mix well. Form in small balls. Flatten with fork. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes and cook until tender.
In large bowl, combine oil, vinegar, salt, mustard, herb seasoning and garlic.

title: fattigman
directions: Flavor with grated lemon rind
and 1 tablespoon or 1 teaspoon cardamon seed, crushed.

title: easy 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight. Add a bit of Cool Whip for a moist consistency.

title: cream cheese don
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk until creamy. Press one package of crescent rolls in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture over rolls, leaving 1/2-inch around the edges.
Layer other package of rolls on top of cream cheese mixture and pinch edges together.
Beat egg white and brush over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, until golden brown. Glaze with powdered sugar and milk.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli dressing
directions: Cook chicken with salt and pepper.
(Deskin chicken before cooking.)
After chicken is cooked, chop in bite-size pieces. Layer bottom of baking dish with chicken.
Make stuffing according to directions on box.
Spread on top of chicken.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Spread on top of Stove Top.
Mix soup and broth and pour on top.
Cover with plain bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add orange juice, then oranges and pineapple.

title: haystack
directions: Brown hamburg in skillet.
Place in bottom of casserole. Place a layer of sliced onions, carrots and potatoes on top of hamburg.
Empty undiluted mushroom soup and tomato soup on top layer.
Do not stir.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine shortening, sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat on medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended; beat in egg. Combine flour, salt and baking soda in small bowl. Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until just slightly blended. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies (they will look light and moist; do not overbake), 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies. Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet. Remove to wire rack. Cool completely. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, except sugar.
Blend sugar and oil; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Add carrots and vanilla.
Pour into a tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: 8 day pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with boiling water four mornings straight. Make sure the cukes are completely under water.

title: chicken-pork loaf
directions: Grind the chicken, pork, chorizo, onion, tomatoes and bread crumbs.
Mix thoroughly the salt, eggs, ground pepper and milk. Now add all the ingredients and mix well.
Pack into a greased loaf pan or other Pyrex casserole.
Steam or bake in a moderate oven (350° to 375°) until the loaf is firm but not too dry.
Slice and serve.

title: chicken casserole with poppy seed
directions: Place chicken in bottom of dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Add poppy seed to crackers.
Place on top of soup layer.
Melt margarine; pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 7 1/2 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange baby carrots
directions: Heat to boiling first 4 ingredients.
Then add drained carrots.
Cook until thoroughly heated.

title: cherry chill
directions: Combine cereal and margarine and press firmly in a 13x9 pan. Beat whipping cream in a chilled mixing bowl until stiff.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Fold whipped cream and marshmallows into cream cheese mixture.
Spread in pan. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Spread pie filling over the top.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Prepare 2 cookie sheets.
Beat together butter and sugar until light and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together the cocoa, flour, soda and salt. Fold into butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in the chopped nuts. Chill for 1 hour.
Drop mixture from a teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet while still warm; cool on wire rack.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown turkey; then place in saucepan.
Using smallest holes on shredder, shred only the meat part of the green pepper, throwing the skin away.
Also using smallest holes on shredder, shred onion. Place onion and pepper with their juices along with spaghetti sauce in saucepan with turkey.
Simmer abut 20 minutes or desired thickness.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Cover chicken with water in Dutch oven.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour until tender.
Cool.
Bone and chop. Wash rice well, drain, place rice, water and salt in medium pan and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes until tender.
Spoon rice into 8-inch square baking dish (greased). Combine chicken and all else except cheese.
Mix well.
Spoon over rice.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: italian salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let set at least 4 hours in refrigerator.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Remove crust and flatten bread.
In a medium bowl, mix cream cheese, bacon and lemon zest.
Spread mixture on bread.
Place asparagus spear (cut to bread size) on bread and roll.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until toasted.
They can be cut in half to serve more people.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In large pan put washed chicken.
Cover with water.
Add onion, celery and sage.
Boil until chicken is tender.
Remove and set aside.
Add can of chicken broth, bouillon cubes and butter to water in pan.
Roll out biscuits thinly on floured board.
Cut into slices.
Add to boiling broth.
Turn heat to medium.
Debone chicken and add to pan in pieces.
Cook about 15 or 20 minutes. One can of biscuits will feed 4; two cans will feed a crowd.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook and drain lasagne noodles according to package.
In a medium pot, combine hot water, tomato paste, salt, pepper and rosemary.
Fry beef until brown; drain off grease.
Add garlic and onion and cook until soft and crumbly.
Add to first mixture and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix the following: mayonnaise, soup, cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Add cooked broccoli and mix well. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup crushed Ritz crackers and bake for 45 minutes.

title: old country chicken soup
directions: In large pot, cover chicken with water.
Bring to boil.
Skim off "foam" or pour off and replace water.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Simmer until meat is tender. Remove meat to plate.
Cool enough to handle.
Remove meat from bones.
Return meat to broth.
When ready to serve, add cooked rice, noodles or small pasta shapes (alphabets, orzo, etc.).

title: t-v mix(party mix)
directions: Combine cereals, pretzels and nuts in roaster pan.
Melt butter and bacon drippings and add Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and pour over cereal mixture.
Thoroughly combine seasonings; sprinkle over mixture.
Mix well.
Toast very slowly in a slow oven at 250°
for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes. Makes 4 quarts.

title: shrimp mold 2
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water (let stand for 10 minutes). Heat soup, add dissolved gelatin and softened cream cheese, when melted add all other ingredients.
Pour into mold and refrigerate. Best if refrigerated over night.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs; beat.
Add remaining ingredients and beat like a cake batter.
Spread on cake roll pan that has been well greased and floured.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Loosen and turn onto a towel that is sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Roll up.
Let cool.
Prepare filling.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown and crumble sausage.
Drain.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine. Thaw and drain broccoli. Mix all ingredients with soup and cheese, spreading some cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and add a small amount of milk.
Whip together and refrigerate several hours.

title: bronco brownies
directions: Heat caramels with 1/3 c. evaporated milk and melt, set aside.

title: special "k" bars
directions: Mix, stir and heat peanut butter, sugar and syrup, stirring continually while heating (do not boil).
Pour over 4 cups Special K cereal.
Mix well and put in greased 12 x 15-inch cookie sheets.

title: rosy relish
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and seasonings and bring to rapid boil.
Add fruit and vegetables.
Simmer until fruit thickens and clear.
Add few drops of red coloring.
This takes quite a while and must be stirred often, especially towards the end or it will scorch and that ruins flavor.
Makes 2 pints.
Don't make more than two batches at a time.
Put in hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put flour and meal in mixing bowl.
Put drippings in an iron skillet and heat in oven while you mix the buttermilk with flour and meal.
Pour 2 to 3 tablespoons of drippings in the flour mixture.
Mix well.
Bake until bottom is brown, then turn to broil to brown top.

title: crispy caramel corn
directions: Boil
brown sugar, Karo, oleo and salt 5 minutes.
Take from the
stove	and
add
soda	and
vanilla.
Pour over the popcorn and mix well.
Pour into pans.
Bake in a 250° oven 1 hour.
Stir several times while baking.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and add 3-4 tsp. to 6 oz. boiling water.

title: crunchy vegetable spread
directions: Put vegetables into a small strainer.
Drain well.
Beat cream cheese and lemon juice together until smooth.
Stir in vegetables and pepper.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cut off heads of broccoli, steam and set aside.
Peel the stems and cut them roughly.
In a soup pot on medium heat, add oil.
Put in leeks and broccoli stems and saute a few minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken stock and oregano.
Simmer until broccoli is thoroughly cooked.
Put broccoli mixture by scant cupfuls, into food process or blender and puree.
Over medium heat in soup pot heat butter, stir in flour and mix.
Add broccoli mixture and stir with whisk until soup comes to a simmer.
Add cream and cheese, stirring constantly.
Season to taste; add broccoli heads, bring soup back to simmer and serve.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish and line with whole graham crackers. Mix pudding and milk.
Beat for 2 minutes and then fold in Cool Whip.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic in skillet; drain well.
Mix all ingredients in large casserole and top with cheese.
Bake
30 minutes at 350°.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated or frozen until ready to use.

title: almond joy cake(makes two cakes)
directions: Mix chocolate cake according to instructions on box.
Bake in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans at 350°.
Bring 1 cup Pet milk and 1 cup sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add coconut.
Pour over hot cakes.
Cover completely. Bring 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup Pet milk and 1 stick oleo to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Pour over coconut mixture.
Top with slivered almonds. Tastes like an Almond Joy candy bar.

title: creamy tuna twist
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 3 ingredients until smooth. Add remaining ingredients and toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and remove meat (save broth).
Put partially
precooked
rice into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour 1 cup broth over rice.
Place chicken breasts over rice.
Blend the 2 soups with 1 cup milk and pour over other ingredients in casserole.	Melt
margarine
and
mix
with 1/4 cup broth; add stuffing
mix.
Mix well and place over chicken ingredients in casserole.	Bake
at
350° for about 30 minutes.
This freezes well and makes 8 generous servings.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2 dish. top with cheese slices.
Combine soup with wine.
Stir well. Spoon over chicken and sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake 350 for 45 - 55 minutes.

title: scalloped onions with cheese
directions: Cook onions in boiling water until tender.
Drain well.
Place onions in 1-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add milk and cook over medium heat until mixture boils.
Stir in cheese and pepper.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Pour sauce over onions.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cod with italian crumb topping
directions: Mix together in shallow bowl the bread crumbs, cheese, cornmeal, oil and seasonings. Spray baking pan with no-stick spray. Dip fillets in beaten egg white and roll in crumb mixture until coated. Place in baking dish and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: date candy
directions: Grind dates and raisins in food grinder.
Mix in chopped nuts. Knead with hands; form into a roll.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap in wax paper; chill well.
Cut into slices.

title: chicken paprika with spaetzle
directions: Coat chicken with flour; set aside remaining flour.
Cook chicken in hot oil over medium heat until browned on all sides, 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove chicken.

title: surprise meat balls
directions: Combine ingredients, except bacon.
Mix well.
Shape into large balls; roll in bacon strips.
Bake for 45 minutes in moderate oven.
Freezes well.

title: creole okra
directions: Saute okra, onion and green pepper in oleo 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 2 servings.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and milk alternately, a little at
a time, until well mixed.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Roll into small pieces and let stand at least 4 hours.
Then melt chocolate and paraffin into a small boiler.
When slightly cool, dip each piece of candy into the chocolate mixture on end of toothpick.

title: cucumber complement
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together all ingredients except cucumbers; set aside.
Peel cucumbers. Slice the cucumbers lengthwise into 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick slices. Stack slices in manageable piles and cut entire stack at an angle into 1 1/4-inch wide pieces.
In a medium bowl, toss together cucumbers with sour cream mixture.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Prepare rice.
Mix together the 2 soups, Cheez Whiz and chopped onion.
Fold in broccoli and rice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in covered casserole.

title: apple pan walnut cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
In mixing bowl, combine eggs, vanilla, oil and 1/2 cup nuts.
Mix well.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Stir only until blended.
Smooth batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until cake springs back when lightly touched in center.
Prick warm cake with fork.
Pour hot topping over warm cake.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup nuts.

title: mango chutney
directions: To vinegar, add sugar and bring to a boil.
Add spices, vegetables, mangoes, raisins and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil 30 minutes.
Pack while at boiling point in sterilized jars and seal.
Mangoes just beginning to turn are best selected.

title: pickled green beans(servings:  8)
directions: Cook green beans as directed on package.
Boil together vinegar, sugar, water (from beans), salad oil and seasonings. Pour this sauce over layers of beans and onion.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: cooked apples
directions: Peel and halve apples, enough to cover a 4 quart saucepan. Add water and sugar.
Let boil 2 1/2 minutes covered.
Reduce heat and let simmer until soft.

title: lemon french chicken
directions: Lay chicken in casserole platter.
Spread onion, pepper, mushrooms and celery over top of chicken.
Sprinkle oil, Worcestershire and lemon juice over.
Add French dressing and salt and pepper.
Cover and cook at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: First, mix eggs, sugar and shortening.
Add peanut butter; then add dry ingredients.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put milk in a large mixing bowl.
Add the pudding mix and mix on low speed until it thickens.
Add the sour cream and mix until it is mixed well, about 2 minutes.
Fold the whipped topping into this mixture, until it is well blended.

title: salpicao
directions: Put all ingredients in a big bowl and mix very well.
Serve cold with rice and shoestring potatoes.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix sugar and graham crackers.
Stir in melted butter and mix well.
Press firmly in bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Chill for 1 hour or bake crust in 375° oven for about 7 minutes and cool before filling.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and butter for 2 to 3 minutes on High in microwave.
Mix well and pour over cereal, tossing lightly to coat all pieces.
Shake the mixture in a plastic bag or large covered bowl with 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar.
Leave uncovered for an hour to dry.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease casserole.
Lay cutlets over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and spread over cutlets.
Grate cheese and arrange on top.
Sprinkle generously with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: sweet kielbasa
directions: Parboil kielbasa for 20 minutes.
Cut into slices.
Heat brown sugar and honey over low heat until it boils.
Pour over cut sausages.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper; drain.
Place in bottom of 11 x 14-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour 1 can pizza sauce over mixture.
Put on top of this the grated Mozzarella cheese and the mild Cheddar cheese.
Top with the biscuits, pulled apart.
Cook in oven until brown and cheese is bubbly.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, cheese and milk.
Add liquid from asparagus to mushroom soup.
Put one layer of crackers in bottom of pan, then layer asparagus.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Cover with soup.
Repeat until everything is used.
Put layer of cheese and crackers on top.
Pour batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert cake
directions: Break angel food cake in pieces in a
large glass dish. Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
Mix
Dream
Whip, cream
cheese and sugar and layer with
cake
pieces.
Combine strawberries and glaze and spread on top. Refrigerate.

title: jubilation thursday casserole
directions: In large 10 to 12-inch frying pan, melt margarine.
Saute onion until golden brown.
Add soup, milk, mustard and pepper. Add noodles and corned beef; stir.
Put mixture in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumb-margarine mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.
Travels well to pot-luck suppers.
(Similar recipe by Gertrude Stanley.)

title: pork and beans and ground meat casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion.
In greased casserole, put pork and beans, mustard, brown sugar and catsup.
Mix well.
Add meat and onion.
Top with sliced American cheese.
Bake, covered, at 450° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: linguica casserole
directions: Cut linguica into 2-inch chunks. Cube potatoes; slice onion and peppers into thin strips. Dice tomatoes into 1-inch chunks. In a large casserole dish, layer potatoes, onions, peppers and tomatoes. Drizzle oil and sprinkle a little garlic powder, parsley, salt and pepper. Top with linguica. Cover dish and cook at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Mix tomato sauce or puree with olive oil.
Add oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Split muffins into halves. Place on cookie sheet.
Add 2 tablespoons of sauce mixture onto each muffin.
Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for about 12 minutes or until cheese just starts to brown.

title: crock-pot camp stew
directions: Place onions and potatoes in a saucepan.
Cover with lightly salted water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until tender.
Drain well.
Combine onions, potatoes and remaining ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low at least 1 hour.

title: ham, potato and cheese casserole
directions: Cook onion and pepper in butter for 5 minutes.
Add flour. Add milk and cook until thickened.
Add ham, potatoes, salt and pepper; mix.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish and top with cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue "flat jacks"
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add barbecue sauce and Tabasco sauce; simmer.
Separate biscuits into 10 and place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press dough together to form crust. Spread meat mixture over dough; cover with cheese.
Bake at 375° until dough is golden brown.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix in order, put in graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies. Refrigerate.

title: scalloped chicken casserole
directions: Put
cut
up chicken into baking dish.	Make a gravy of butter,
flour
and
broth.
Toss
bread cubes, melted butter, cream,
grated onion, sage, salt and pepper together to make a dressing.
Spread
dressing over the chicken and dribble gravy over the top.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix first five ingredients together in a large bowl with hands.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Then roll in coconut flakes. Store tightly covered in refrigerator.

title: caesar salad
directions: Place garlic cloves, cut in half, in oil and let stand several hours.
Near serving time, drizzle some garlic oil over croutons and toss lightly.
Fifteen minutes before serving, place romaine lettuce broken into fat pieces in salad bowl.
When ready to serve, remove garlic and drizzle oil over greens, then vinegar, lemon juice, Parmesan and seasonings.
Break in coddled egg and roll-toss until every leaf is coated.
Add croutons.
Lightly toss and serve at once.
Serves 6. Preparation time:
1 hour.

title: chili sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to good boil; put in quart jars with large clove on top, then seal.
Great for spaghetti sauce or add beans for chili.

title: spanish fried rice
directions: Saute rice in shortening in a large saucepan over medium heat until rice is lightly browned.
Add tomato, onion and green pepper to rice mixture and saute until vegetables are tender.
Stir chicken broth, minced garlic, salt, cumin seed and pepper into vegetable mixture.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil 1 fryer or 3 or 4 chicken breasts.
Chop chicken into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix broth and soup, pour over chicken (you may want to add boiled eggs).
Melt oleo and add flour and milk.
Mix until thickens.
Pour gently over 1st layer.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 425°.

title: vegetable cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar, egg yolks and hot water.
Add the raw carrots and beets.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites and fold into the creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet and bake according to directions. Cool.
Spread with mixture of cream cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and Hidden Valley dressing; mix well.
Then top with diced broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper, mushrooms, tomatoes or whatever you desire.
Top with various cheeses, if desired (Cheddar and/or Mozzarella cheeses).

title: vegetable soup with meat
directions: * Or cooked, diced fresh chicken.

title: amelia boone's potato cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding mashed potatoes last. Potatoes may be mashed with a little salt and milk but no butter.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a plastic bag. Shake each piece of biscuit in mixture.
In a saucepan, melt together remaining ingredients.
Place biscuits in a Bundt pan and pour sauce over them.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add the taco season package.
Add beans. Simmer 10 minutes.
Chop onion, tomatoes and lettuce.
Add cheese and dressing.
Toss with hamburger and tortilla chips.
Serve immediately.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in tightly sealed container.
Use 1/3 to 1/2 cup mix with boiling water for 1 cup hot chocolate. Yields enough to share with a friend.

title: saucy beef casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook the beef and onion over medium heat until meat is brown.
Stir in the soups.
Transfer to a greased 8 inch pan.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles and bake for 5 minutes longer or until noodles are crisp.

title: quick and easy chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken and Veg-All; cut up margarine on top of this. Mix canned milk with soup and pour on top, then mix milk with Bisquick and pour on top of that mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: georgia candy cookies
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together.
Press in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips over hot water.
Spread over top of cookies.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Cut in small squares (I leave in refrigerator overnight, then leave out until chocolate can be cut without cracking).

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix.
Put in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: blue hawaiian
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with cherry and pineapple chunk.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Add flour and chili powder, stirring while adding.
Add enchilada sauce and water. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Fry tortillas and dip in sauce.
Layer torts, cheese and sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Begin sauce; end cheese. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: fresh fried potatoes
directions: Pare 3 medium potatoes; slice thin and season.
Fry covered in 3 tablespoons bacon drippings or other fat for 10 minutes. Uncover and brown other side about 10 minutes, loosening occasionally.

title: lemon jello pound cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, lemon jello, eggs, oil, water and sugar.
Beat until creamy and smooth.
Pour into a tube pan and bake for 45 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush crackers and sprinkle bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix instant pudding with crushed pineapple and juice until thick. Pour mixture over crumbs.
Add bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: girdle buster
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Whip softened cream cheese with sugar, eggs and vanilla (may be somewhat lumpy).
Using foil muffin cups, place one cookie in bottom of cup.
Fill cup about 2/3 to 3/4 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden or splitting occurs.
Cool.
Spoon fruit topping on each.
Chill. Makes 15 to 18 tarts.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Mix brown sugar, ginger and garlic powder.
Add soy sauce, then add water.
Cut wings at joint; cut tips off.
Marinate wings overnight or at least 8 hours.
Bake in a foil lined pan at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain and save juice from clams; put juice in 2-cup measuring cup.
Fill with water to make 2 cups liquid.
Fry bacon until crisp (chopped); set aside.
Cook potatoes, chopped onions and spices in 2 cups of liquid; when potatoes are done, add margarine, flour, milk, bacon and clams.
Stir.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados into a mush with a fork.
Blend in other ingredients with a fork.
Taste and season (additional salt, garlic and chili) to your liking.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: chocolate or white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cocoa in at least 4-quart kettle. Stir, adding milk, until tests to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter, butter and nuts.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: pud's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and butter together.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful and flatten with a wet fork. Bake at 350°.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl, except butter.
Pour over chicken. Then cut up butter all over chicken.
Start cooking at 350°, then lower to 325° for 2 hours.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add beaten eggs.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add pineapple, cherries, dates and pecans. Mix all together.
(Can use hands.)

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients, then add the remaining 6 ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: beef barbecues
directions: Cook at 475° for 20 minutes.
Turn down heat to 325° and cook 3 to 4 hours.
You may want to thicken sauce a little.
Shred meat. Serve over buns.

title: cheese stuffing for manicotti
directions: Cook 1 (14 count) box of manicotti in boiling water for 8 minutes; drain and rinse in cold water.

title: three-cheese enchiladas
directions: Combine 1 cup of Monterey Jack cheese, 1 cup of Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and 1/4 cup of picante sauce.
Saute bell pepper and green onions.
Drain off butter and add to cheese mixture.
Add cumin and mix well.

title: adobo
directions: Bring all to a boil in large pot.
Let it cook on medium-high until done.
Serve over plain white rice.

title: potluck pan rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1/2 cup water.
Add butter, eggs, milk powder, salt, 3 cups flour and remaining sugar and water.
Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes or until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to form soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface, knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down. Divide into 27 pieces and shape into balls.
Place 18 balls in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan and the remaining balls in a greased 9 inch square baking pan.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 375 degrees for 17 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream together cream cheese and butter first, then add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth and well blended. Makes enough for 2 layer cake.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage, onion and green peppers. Drain.
Add to the tomatoes, corn and cheese.
Bake 1 hour in moderate oven (350°). Add macaroni, if desired.

title: homemade bread
directions: Add yeast and warm water in bowl.
Add Crisco or butter, salt, sugar and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with mixer.
Add rest of flour and blend with spoon until nice and smooth.
Cover with cloth and let rise in warm place for about 30 minutes.
Knead 25 strokes and spread even in greased loaf pan. Pat in shape with back of hand.
Let rise.
Put in oven at 375° until brown, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Generously grease large baking sheet; set aside.
Combine sugar and corn syrup in 2-quart glass measure.
Cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts with wooden spoon.
Cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook on High 2 minutes. Add baking soda; stir until mixture is light and foamy.
Pour onto prepared baking sheet.
Spread quickly to edges.
Cool completely before breaking into pieces.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Sourdough hotcakes, the main breakfast dish of Alaskan prospectors, differ from other breads or hotcakes because the batter is leavened with yeast starter and soda.
The starter must set 36 hours before it is to be used.
Replenished regularly with flour and water, the starter will last weeks, even years.
Some Alaskans are still using the starter traced back to an original starter brought into the state with the gold rush.
To them the sourdough pot is prized possession.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients but potatoes and refrigerate.
Just before serving, add potatoes.

title: stacked enchiladas
directions: Warm sauces in large frypan.
Dip tortilla in sauce.
Place in flat bottom casserole dish same size as tortillas.
Top with 1/4 browned hamburger, diced onion and grated cheese.
Repeat, ending with tortilla.
Top with remaining sauce and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
Slice like pie.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix meat, salt and ginger and roll into small balls.
Dip in egg; roll in flour.
Fry in hot oil; remove from pan.
Drain fat from pan.
Drain and reserve pineapple juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup liquid.
Stir liquid into pan, scraping bottom of pan.
Blend cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar and brown sugar; stir into pineapple juice.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add meatballs.
Add pineapple chunks.
Cover meatballs with green pepper rings; cover and cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt and pour the chocolate chips and butter over the cereal. Add peanut butter to the mix and stir.
Put in a plastic bag with powdered sugar and shake to combine the ingredients.
Eat right out of the bag just like potato chips.

title: yummy fruit salad
directions: Cut watermelon and cantaloupe into chunks.
Cut strawberries in half.
Mix the 3 gently by hand.
Add pineapple and blueberries. Chill.
Add sliced bananas just before serving.

title: fruit freezes
directions: You will also need wooden sticks.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Batter will be stiff. Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar mixture over top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in a large, heavy kettle over medium heat.
Add the onions and salt and cook over low heat, stirring frequently, about 20 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Sprinkle the flour over the onions and stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.

title: herb biscuits
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Add milk all at once. Stir with a fork into soft dough.
Beat 15 strokes.
It will be stiff and sticky.
Roll dough around board lightly dusted with Bisquick to prevent sticking.
Knead gently 8 to 10 times to smooth up dough.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter that has been dipped in Bisquick.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: buttery pan rolls
directions: Boil potato until soft.
Peel and mash.
Measure 1 cup into large bowl.
Mix in 2/3 cup shortening, sugar, eggs and salt. Sprinkle yeast over 1/2 cup lukewarm water in small bowl; stir to dissolve.
Stir yeast and milk into potato mixture.
Mix enough flour, 1/2 cup at a time, to make a firm but slightly sticky dough. Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Grease large bowl.
Add dough, turning to coat.
Cover and let rise in warm draft-free area until doubled in volume, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream salmon
directions: Place
fish in 14-inch Dutch oven, skin side down.
Rub with salt
and pepper.
Mix onion, sour cream and lemon juice. Spread on	fish.
Bake for 30 minutes with 12 coals on the top and 10 coals on the bottom.

title: fannie wilson's mahogany cake
directions: Mix well.
Spread between layers and on top of cake.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage, onions and bell pepper.
Drain well.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Place half of the biscuits in greased Bundt pan; cover with half of sausage mixture, then half of cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 375° oven.
Serve warm.
Good with scrambled eggs.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large casserole dish.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour 3 times.
Add soda and cream of tartar.
Cream butter and sugar until very light and add to the stiffly beaten egg whites gradually.
Add the flour, beating it lightly.
Flavor with teaspoon of vanilla.
Place in angel food pan and bake in slow oven at about 250°.
Top with fresh fruit.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat and bone from meat; cut meat into pieces. Brown meat thoroughly in butter; season with salt. Add onions; cook until tender. Stir in broth, soy sauce and garlic. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until meat is tender. Add green peppers; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Blend cornstarch and water; stir gradually into meat mixture, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Boil 1 minute, then add tomatoes; heat through. Serve over rice.

title: stuffed peach halves
directions: Mix together enough crumbs, pecans, sugar and syrup to make a spread-like consistency.
Fill peach halves.
Bake at 300°
for 15 minutes.
Broil briefly until brown and bubbly.
Serve as a side dish with chicken.

title: salsa
directions: Place about half of the tomatoes and their liquid, bell pepper, garlic, jalapenos and onion in a blender or food processor and whirl until finely chopped.
Pour into a 5 to 6-quart pan. Finely chop remaining tomatoes, bell pepper, garlic, jalapenos and onion and add to pan.
Stir in tomato puree, wine, sugar, wine vinegar, distilled vinegar, pepper, basil, cayenne and Worcestershire.
Bring to a boil over high heat; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring often until mixture is reduced to about 3 quarts, about 30 minutes.
Add salt to taste.
Let cool, then serve.
Or store to use as needed; ladle salsa into refrigerator or freezer containers (1 to 2-cup size) and cover. Store in the refrigerator up to 2 weeks or freeze for longer storage.
Makes about 11 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts. Make Rice-A-Roni according to directions. Then stir in broth, cans of soup, along with chopped chicken. Add 1 cup of the chicken broth. Melt some butter and mix with enough stuffing to cover top of casserole. Bake for 30 minutes between 325° and 350°.

title: apple pork chops
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a shallow bowl.
Dredge pork chops in mixture.
Reserve remaining flour mixture.
Brown chops in oil in large skillet.
Arrange chops in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Core unpeeled apples and cut into rings.
Place on chops. Pour 1 1/2 cups apple juice over apples.
Combine sugar and allspice; sprinkle over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for one hour or until chops are tender.
Remove pork chops and apple slices to a serving platter.
Reserve pan drippings.
Dissolve 1 1/2 tablespoons remaining flour mixture in remaining 1/2 cup apple juice.
Combine flour mixture and pan drippings in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Serve sauce over chops.
Yields 6 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to a rolling boil butter, sugar, cocoa and milk for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoons on wax paper.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
This is excellent for parties.

title: banana chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all together and spread on greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: german casserole
directions: When browning hamburger, add the dry onion soup mix.
Cook the wild rice according to directions.
Simmer the sauerkraut with 1 cup of water for about 20 minutes.
Drain.

title: never fail pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in heavy 10-inch skillet or square pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter.
Arrange pineapple in pattern over brown sugar.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together; add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add egg; beat 2 more minutes.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Turn cake upside-down on serving plate.
Leave pan over cake for 10 minutes.
Remove pan; serve warm.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Add sugar, cocoa, soda, salt and flour.
Stir well to blend. Add mayonnaise and stir; add water and vanilla, then beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Place sliced potatoes on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Put in layer of onions.
Place pork chops next.
If need be, layer potatoes and onions again.
Add pepper to taste.
Spread cream of mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix together the sugar, margarine and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Gradually add flour; mix in milk and vanilla. Beat for about 10 minutes.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, then at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not preheat oven.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil.
Combine soups, tomatoes, cheese and garlic salt.
Heat until well mixed and add to onion and pepper.
Tear up tortillas and layer with chicken in pan (9 x 13-inch rectangular works well).
Pour soup mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Whisk first 3 ingredients.
Mix next 4 ingredients and then add chips.
Bake in sprayed bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn out of pan immediately.

title: carrot and apple salad
directions: Peel, core and chop apples.
Grate carrots.
Mix peanut butter and mayonnaise and blend with other ingredients.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Chop orange slice candy and dates.
Add pecans and coconut. Add 1/2 cup flour and coat.
In large bowl mix sugar and shortening until light, add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour and soda, beat well, add buttermilk.
Beat well.
Fold in chopped fruit and nuts.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 275 degrees.

title: scalloped tomatoes and cheese
directions: Place tomatoes in a buttered casserole dish.
Stir in salt, sugar, thyme, bay leaf, basil and crumbled bread.
Mix grated cheese and curry powder.
Sprinkle over tomatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: baked macaroni with broccoli
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Preheat oven to 300° to 350°. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese; mix well. Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Cover and bake 55 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Uncover; top with cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes.
Leave skin on.
Dice potatoes and boil until tender, approximately 6 to 7 minutes.
Drain.
Place potatoes in baking dish.
Pour Ranch dressing over potatoes. Cover well. Top with grated cheese.
Place in warm oven until cheese melts.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti. Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs. Form into a
crust in a 10-inch buttered pie pan.
Spread cottage cheese over crust. Cook hamburger, onion and pepper. Drain.
Add tomatoes, paste, sugar, oregano, salt and garlic. Simmer. Add to pie crust and cottage cheese mixture.
Cover with foil.
Let sit in refrigerator 2 to 24 hours. Bake, covered, at 350° for 60 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Bring chicken to a boil.
When done, debone and dice in small pieces.
Add to cooked spaghetti in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, add cheese, soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Heat in microwave until cheese is thoroughly melted.
When done, pour over chicken and spaghetti.
Mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: ruby's chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Spread cookie mixture on greased 11 x 16 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 325° until done, about 15 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares to serve.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Put into greased casserole dish.
Place layer of tomatoes, half of cucumbers and crumbs.
Repeat.
Top with tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with buttercream or cream cheese frosting when completely cool.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in butter. Add garlic powder to taste. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour, stirring so it will not stick.

title: fresh fruit salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: In a small bowl, mix the yogurt and poppy seed.
Pour over fruit and serve.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix dry ingredients in one bowl and liquid ingredients in another.
Gradually mix together well.
Pour into greased, floured tube pan or spray pan with Pam.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: bran muffin mix
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients. Add milk, nuts and raisins. Bake in muffin tins 20 minutes at 400°. Will keep in sealed containers in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: chicken devine
directions: Partially cook broccoli.
Put chicken and broccoli in greased 13 x 9 pan.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry in sauce pan on low heat.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs on the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rum, berry treat
directions: Blend for about 30 seconds or until smooth.
Serve over ice. Makes 16 ounces.

title: shrimp and feta linguine
directions: Saute the onion, then add everything but the Feta and shrimp. Simmer to thicken (how long depends on you).
Stir in crumbled cheese and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add the shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes (less is better).
Serve over noodles or rice.
Top with parsley.
Very easy, particularly if you find shrimp already peeled and cleaned.
Serves 4.

title: swiss cherry cheese torte cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on box in 2 (8-inch) round layers. When cooled, split layers into two layers so you have 4 layers. Beat together cream cheese and lemon juice until smooth.
Fold in vanilla frosting.
Spread vanilla frosting mixture and cherry pie filling between each layer and on top.
Refrigerate.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan; add brown sugar.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and continue to cook, stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Gradually add confectioners sugar until frosting is of desired consistency to spread.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in a large mixing bowl at medium speed until light and fluffy, scraping sides of bowl.
Then mix at high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan of choice.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together all ingredients except Cool Whip.
Fold Cool Whip in.
Pour into baked pie shell. Refrigerate 2 hours. Cool Whip can be put on top before serving.

title: diet salad dressing
directions: Mix first eight ingredients in a blender.
Drizzle in slowly the salad oil and Hidden Valley dressing.
Use only 1 tablespoon daily.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Mix soup, milk and rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken on top and sprinkle dry soup on top of chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Don't peek.

title: pudding cake
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar and press in pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown turkey in a skillet with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 can corn (drained).
Add taco mix.
Add tomatoes and set aside.
Mix cornbread as directed; add other 1/2 can corn.
Pour this into a Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour meat mixture over this.
Then put the cheese over meat mixture.
Spread remaining batter over this and bake until cornbread is done in about a 425° oven.

title: penne provencale
directions: Cook penne in boiling water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon oil to prevent from sticking.
Saute chopped onion, garlic and pepper.
Then add chopped tomatoes.
When tender, add to pasta.
Add mushrooms, olives and tuna.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs, grated cheese and optional nuts.
Dribble with olive oil and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until hot.

title: kabsa(saudi chicken and rice skillet)
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Add chicken pieces.
Saute until onion is tender. Stir in tomato sauce or puree.
Simmer over low heat 1 minute to blend flavors. Add tomatoes, carrots, orange peel, cloves, cardamom, cinnamon stick, salt and pepper. Cook 1 minute.
Add broth.
Return chicken pieces to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer over low heat 30 minutes.
Stir rice into liquid between pieces of chicken.
Or remove chicken, stir in rice, then return chicken pieces to skillet.
Cover tightly and simmer 30 minutes longer or until rice is tender. Carefully fluff the rice and garnish with raisins and almonds. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir in carrots, raisins, pecans, coconut and apples.
In bowl, beat eggs with vegetable oil and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture until just combined.

title: hot potato salad with bacon
directions: Put the potatoes in a large pot of boiling water.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender.
Drain.
When cool enough to handle, peel and cut into chunks.
Cook bacon in a large frying pan until crisp.
Drain on paper towels and crumble.
Measure the bacon fat; add oil to make 1/2 cup and return to pan.
Slice the scallion and cook in the fat until softened, about 30 seconds. Add the vinegar, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Immediately pour the entire contents of the pan over the potatoes and toss to coat.
Add the crumbled bacon.
Taste for seasoning and salt and pepper, if needed.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Cool, then crumble. Mix pudding according to package; line bottom of bowl with crumbled cake, then layer with ingredients until all are used, cake, pineapple, cherry filling and pudding.
Keep repeating all ingredients in order.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.
Can cut ingredients in half for small dessert.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter.
Let cool.
Mix all other ingredients into butter.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 pie.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine meat, cheese, soup and milk with onion.
Alternate layers of macaroni and mixture in a 2-quart casserole and top with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine 1/2 c sugar and 1/2 c water in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil to softball stage. Add 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice and 2 c chopped, fresh strawberries. Boil 1 min longer and remove form heat. Chill until serving time. This is good on vanilla ice cream and on strawberry shortcake.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions in water for 1 hour.
Put vinegar, spices and sugar together and boil for 5 minutes.
Add drained cucumbers and onions; boil for 5 minutes.
Place in jars while hot and seal.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in reserved juice.
Add cheese and pineapple; mix well.
Spoon mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: s'mores
directions: On paper toweling, place 1 graham cracker square.
Top with a chocolate square, then marshmallow.
Place in microwave oven.
Set cook cycle 1 for 0:15 minutes at High power.
Cook S'More.
Top with second graham cracker square.
Let stand for 1 minute before serving.
Makes 1 serving.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add mixed dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating after each addition. Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch), rubbed with Crisco and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Cool cake in pan on rack 15 minutes.
Before removing, loosen sides from pan with spatula.
Remove cake and spread with frosting, fruit or favorite sauce.

title: chilies rellenos bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain fat.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Place half the chilies on bottom of a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with meat mixture; arrange the remaining green chilies on top.
Combine eggs, milk, flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over chilies.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven (preheated) for 45 minutes, or until cheese is browned and a knife inserted into the dish comes out clean.
Serve with taco sauce.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Let the boiling water and tea bags set for 5 minutes.
Combine all ingredients and freeze.
When serving, use 1/2 mix to 1/2 slush. Top with maraschino cherry.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
When layers have cooled, split them in two with thread.
Then mix sugar, sour cream and thawed coconut together.
Set aside 1 cup of mixture. Put remaining mixture between the layers.
Add 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip to the cup of reserved mixture, to frost the cake. Refrigerate 3 days in an airtight container.

title: broccoli with stuffing
directions: Cook broccoli.
Combine eggs, onion, soup and mayonnaise. Place layer of broccoli in a 2-quart casserole.
Add layer of cheese.
Pour small amount of sauce on top.
Repeat layers until all is used.
Top with stuffing mix.
Pour melted oleo on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry cheese salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed and chill until gelled.
Combine berries and sugar.
Fold into half of jello; chill until firm. Whip remaining jello and fold into softened cream cheese.
Add nuts.
Spread on top of first mixture.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix margarine (oil) and dry ingredients.
Add bananas and nuts. Beat eggs and add.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
For mini loaves (3), bake less than 40 minutes.

title: baked alaska
directions: Prepare cake recipe as directed.
Pour batter into a 9-inch greased square pan; bake as directed.
Remove from pan and cool. Cut in half horizontally (save half for future use).
Place on heatproof platter.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar; mix in.
Add sugar gradually, continuing to beat until egg whites form stiff peaks.
Remove ice cream from container.
Round ice cream corners with small spatula.
Place on cake.
Cover ice cream and cake generously with meringue.
Be sure to smooth and cover entire surface.
Working quickly, fill pastry bag with meringue.
Using rosette tip, decorate.
Place in preheated oven at 400° for 3 minutes or until meringue just begins to turn brown. Serve immediately.
Makes 18 servings.

title: madelyn's taco dip
directions: Melt margarine in large frying pan.
Saute onion until tender. Do not brown.
Add tomato and chilies.
Saute until tomato is soft.
Add cream cheese and stir until well blended.
Serve warm or cold with tortilla chips.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and margarine until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, and blend well.
Add flour, salt and milk, alternating dry mixture with milk.
Add vanilla. Mix until well blended.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broken glass gelatin salad
directions: Prepare red, orange and lime Jell-O separately, using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each flavor.
Pour each flavor separately into 8-inch pans.
Chill until firm or overnight.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with enough water to equal a gallon. Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: fig bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and cut in margarine and egg.
Add nuts, coconut and flavorings.
Divide mixture in half.
Spread half on bottom of greased and floured pan.
Cover with fig jam. Spread with other half of mixture.
Bake at 350° until nicely brown.

title: ritz treats
directions: Melt chocolate chips in microwave 2 minutes; stir.
If not completely melted, continue to melt at 30 second intervals.
Do not overcook.
Dip Ritz in chocolate and place on wax paper until chocolate hardens.
(Vanilla baking squares may be used.)

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam; sprinkle 1 1/2 cups crushed corn chips in the pan.
Layer with chicken.
Mix the tomatoes and chillies with the 2 cans of soup and onion; add 1 cup shredded cheese.
Mix well and pour over the chicken.
Add remaining 1/2 cup crushed corn chips over the top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: quick brunswick stew
directions: Combine all the ingredients and cook slowly for 30 minutes or until heated through and flavors are well blended.
Freezes well.

title: chile con queso dip
directions: Melt cheese in crock pot. Add sausage and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Mix well. Serve with chips.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in salted boiling water 5 minutes. Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots.
Fold in squash and onions.
Combine stuffing mix and butter spreading 1/2 in well-greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon veggie mixture on top.
Top with rest of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Saute shrimp meat in melted butter over low heat for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle in flour; add cream (half and half) slowly, stirring constantly, until sauce boils.
Add sherry and egg yolks and cook for about 1 minute.
Do not overcook because sauce will curdle.
Season with cayenne and salt.
Serve in patty shells.

title: date pecan bars
directions: Combine margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Combine baking soda and water.
Add to beaten mixture.
Add vanilla and dash of salt, then add dates, cherries and pecans. Mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Press dough in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely in pan. Cut into bars.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples with sugar.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Stir into apples and sugar.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add nuts and stir well.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broiled carp
directions: Mix yellow cornmeal with seasoning salt, garlic salt and black pepper.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Combine ingredients in brown paper bag; shake until fish is covered well.
Place one 9 x 12-inch piece of plywood on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes. Remove from oven, throw fish away, cut plywood into 4 pieces. Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers and cut in half lengthwise; remove seeds. Crumble beef into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; add onion.
Cook uncovered on high for 5 minutes, stirring once during cooking. Cook until meat turns brown.
Stir in salt, pepper, rice and half of tomato sauce.
Fill green pepper halves with mixture.
Place in casserole dish.
Top each pepper with remaining tomato sauce. Cover; cook on high 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.

title: garlic cheese grits casserole
directions: Stir butter and 1 cup cheese into hot grits until melted. Add eggs, milk and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese and top with broiled sausage. Return to oven only until cheese melts.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in large pan over medium heat.
Add onion.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Add broccoli; cover and bring to boil again.
Reduce heat; cook about 10 minutes until broccoli is tender.
Sprinkle cheese into broccoli.
Allow it to melt.
Combine milk and flour (I shake it in a gravy shaker).
Pour milk mixture into broccoli, stirring to combine.
Continue cooking over medium heat until soup comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
(Do not allow soup to stay on heat once it comes to a boil, since the milk will curdle.)

title: cheerios candy
directions: Melt chocolate, combine nuts & Cheerios.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: dirty rice(servings: 6.  preparation time: 1 hour and 30 minutes.)
