directions: Bring stock to a boil with onion, celery and garlic.
Add giblets and livers; lower heat and simmer until livers are just done, but still pink inside.
Drain, reserving stock.
Coarsely chop livers and edible giblets and reserve.

title: icebox pecan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and place in refrigerator to harden.
When relatively hard, remove and mold into oblong bar. Cover with wax paper and let stand in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Cut into thin slices and bake in hot oven (400°) for about 10 minutes.

title: farmer's breakfast
directions: Fry bacon; cut in small strips.
Save 3 tablespoons of grease in skillet.
Place green peppers and onion in skillet.
Place potatoes in skillet; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Fry until golden brown, stirring often.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Break 6 eggs over potatoes in pan and cook at low heat until eggs are set.
Stir constantly.
Serves 6.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and flour together, making a crumbly mixture.
Put peaches with juice in baking dish and then sprinkle crumbly mixture over peaches.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: lemon cake pudding(made with lemon, lime, orange or pineapple.)
directions: Sift together into mixing bowl the flour, sugar and salt. Stir in lemon rind, lemon juice, egg yolks and milk. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole (7 1/2-inch) or 6 custard cups. Set in pan of water (1-inch deep). Bake.
Serve warm or cold with or without whipped cream.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: sun tea
directions: In a glass jar, combine the tea and cold water.
Cover and steep in the sun several hours.
Serve it in tall glasses with ice and lemon, if desired.

title: blueberry shortcake
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour, egg and buttermilk.
Drop by large spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: microwave pecan brittle
directions: Mix pecans, sugar, corn syrup and salt in glass mixing bowl. Cook 8 minutes on High.
Mixture should be bubbly and nuts brown (time varies, if hot microwave, lessen 1 minute).
Quickly stir in butter and vanilla, cook 2 1/2 minutes longer.
Add baking soda and stir quickly, just until it is foamy.
Pour on greased baking sheet; let cool.

title: crab imperial
directions: Remove all shells from crabmeat.
Mix all ingredients except crab and paprika.
Gently stir mixture into crabmeat.
Put in greased shells or shallow baking dish that has been greased.

title: bread sauce for wild fowl
directions: Stud onion with cloves.
Place in saucepan with milk, cayenne and salt.
Bring to boil; simmer about 5 minutes and strain.
Add bread crumbs; stir in butter.
Serve with any game bird.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake and pudding mix according to package directions. Grind Skor candy bars.
Cut cake into 3 layers.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Beat first 2 ingredients together until blended.
Add eggs (beat).
Gradually add sugars; beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9-inch pan; for a 13 x 9-inch pan, double the recipe and bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Finely chop vegetables and mix everything together.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Gently mix all ingredients.
Serve in salad bowl.

title: grilled chicken sandwiches
directions: To make marinade: Use the proportions of 1/3 pineapple juice to 2/3 bottled teriyaki sauce, for one or two chicken breast.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine; set aside.
Cook broccoli and drain; mix with rice, cream of chicken soup and Cheez Whiz.
Add sauteed onions and celery.
Put into casserole. Put crumbled cooked bacon on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peppernuts
directions: Cream sugar and butter; beat eggs and add to sugar mixture. Add cream.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add enough flour to make soft dough (not sticky).
Mix well.
Chill dough 4 hours. Roll dough into long rolls, about 1/2-inch diameter.
Cut into tiny pieces and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for about 8 minutes or until slightly brown.
(Cutting is much easier if the long rolls of dough are frozen.)

title: icebox cloverleaf rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over lard.
When melted, add cold water, beaten egg and sugar.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to first mixture.
Add salt and flour.
Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours or overnight.

title: guinea hens with orange sauce
directions: Cut guinea hens into serving pieces; season with salt and pepper.
Brown in butter in ovenproof skillet.
Peel and quarter oranges.
Add orange quarters and rind to mixture in skillet. Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/2 cup hot water.
Combine bouillon liquid and wine.
Add to guinea hen mixture.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.
Serve with sauce over wild or white rice. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut lover's bread
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in peanut butter and eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.
Add flour and milk, pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: quicky cheese pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a blender.
Blend until creamy, pour in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for about 30 minutes; mix sour cream and 2 tablespoons of sugar in a bowl.
Set aside.

title: chicken pie in potato crust
directions: Thaw potatoes by pouring boiling water over them; drain well. Pat dry with paper towel.
In bowl, combine potatoes and 6 tablespoons melted butter or margarine.
Press mixture in bottom and up sides of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.

title: paul's beef stroganoff
directions: In butter, brown strip steak that has been thinly sliced.
Add onion, mushrooms and garlic.
Add flour.
Add water to desired thickness; boil.
When boiled to desired thickness, (add more water if you want it thinner), take off heat.
Add sour cream. Serve over egg noodles.

title: pineapple-orange punch
directions: Combine juice and water; add sherbet and blend.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 12.

title: andrew's french pancakes
directions: Measure out dry ingredients; add 2 cups milk and stir.
Add margarine and eggs; stir.
Add more milk until a thin consistency. Cook as normal pancakes.
They should be flat like crepes.
Serve with fruit (a berry sauce is a favorite).
Top with fruit, roll and top with powdered sugar.

title: date refrigerator pinwheels
directions: Combine dates, sugar and water and cook over low flame until thick (about 10 minutes).
Add nuts and cool.
Meanwhile, cream shortening until fluffy; add brown sugar gradually while continuing to cream.
Add well beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients sifted together and mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Divide mixture into 2 parts and roll each out separately into a rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
Spread each half with half of date filling and roll as for jelly roll into 2 long rolls. Chill overnight.
Cut with sharp knife into slices 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on greased sheet at 400°
for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Cream sugar and soft cream cheese.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Place in 18 paper cupcake liners and put in muffin tins.
Fill with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° or 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely and top with cherry or blueberry pie filling.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix oil and garlic and let stand about 2 hours.
Discard the garlic.
Put the lettuce and croutons in wooden salad bowl. Combine all remaining ingredients, except cheese, and shake together well with the garlic oil.
Pour over the salad and toss. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: coke salad
directions: Bring water, sugar, gelatin and Coke to a boil. Add cherry pie filling, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into lightly oiled 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Mix all together. Keep in sealed container. Will keep in fridge a week. It's nice for finger sandwiches on party rye or wheat bread.

title: mashed baked potatoes
directions: Beat all together.
Bake, uncovered, for one hour.

title: katie's freezer green beans(how to freeze and cook them)
directions: You will need Ziploc bags, colander and dishpan (need large pan to prepare beans for freezer).

title: easy lemon icebox pie
directions: Thaw out lemonade.
Mix Cool Whip, milk and lemonade together in a large bowl.
Pour into ready-made pie crusts.
Makes 3 pies. Refrigerate for about 2 hours.
Take out and eat.

title: pineapple gala
directions: Crumb cookies and mix with butter or margarine.
Line a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan with mixture and chill an hour or more.
Fill pan with
2 quarts of soft sherbet.
Top with chopped nuts or your choice of garnish.

title: lasagna
directions: Note:
Use 8 x 8-inch glass pan.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Make Jell-O and pudding according to package directions.
Cook pudding.
Slightly jell the Jell-O to 1/2 done.
Mix the cooled pudding and Jell-O together, then layer Jell-O/pudding mixture, then Cool Whip, then Jell-O/pudding mixture, ending with Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with coconut.

title: aloha loaf
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs, mixing well.

Add the mashed bananas and flour, sifted together with the baking powder, soda and salt. Fold in undrained pineapple and coconut. Bake in two greased 9 x 5 loaf pans in 350° oven for one hour and 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients, then mix all.
Place in two greased and floured pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
(Check at 45 minutes.)

title: wayne's meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Form into balls of same size.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° until brown all the way through, approximately 30 minutes.
Serve with barbecue sauce, spaghetti sauce or with Sweet and Sour Sauce (recipe follows).

title: play clay to make ornaments
directions: Mix soda and cornstarch together, blending well.
Add the cold water and mix well until mixture is smooth.
Boil for 1 minute until it has consistency of moist mashed potatoes.
Stir constantly.
Spoon out on a plate.
Cover with a damp cloth and allow to cool.
Knead dough and roll out on waxed paper.
Cut out with cookie cutter or shape by hand.
Let dry 2 or 3 days.
Paint with water color paint or food color (small children).
Dry well. coat now with clear shellac or clear nail polish.
Hangers can be mounted on back with glue or pressed into back before they dry.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in medium bowl.
Stir well.
Spoon into lightly-greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Toss gently.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings. (May be made day ahead, refrigerated, then baked as needed.)

title: cheese and herb stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Mix cream cheese, dressing mix, mayonnaise, onion, parsley and Parmesan cheese. Fill mushrooms with mixture and dip in crushed stuffing.
Place on buttered baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 325° until heated through, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sister-in-law's heath bar cake
directions: Make cake and bake per box directions. Make pudding according to package directions. Grind Heath Bars in blender. After cake is cooled, crumble. Layer cake, pudding, Heath Bars, and Cool Whip in glass dish. Chill.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk, egg and other ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: ham delight
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake until hot at 375°.

title: brown sugar french toast
directions: Melt in 13 x 9-inch pan the butter, maple syrup and brown sugar.
Slice apples on top; cover apples with thick slices of Italian or French bread.
In blender, mix eggs, vanilla and milk. Pour over bread; refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can use peaches also.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir in brown sugar. Arrange pineapple slices or crushed pineapple in pan.
Arrange sliced cherries.
Mix yellow cake mix according to directions, except substitute juice for water.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test with cake tester.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: busy day goulash
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat.
Add all the rest of the ingredients and simmer until spaghetti is cooked.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Pull off the bone.
Put potatoes, onions and carrots in food processor to shred.
Then put everything but noodles together and cook for 30 minutes.
When that is done, add noodles and cook until noodles are done.

title: taco salad
directions: Add chopped onion and shredded cheese to shredded lettuce in a large bowl.
Keep cold.

title: dream salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Soften Cool Whip. Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail together.
Add chopped nuts if desired.
Chill until served.

title: macaroni-tuna salad
directions: Cook and cool the macaroni; mix all ingredients with salad dressing.
Serve chilled on a lettuce leaf.

title: dump cake
directions: Put filling on bottom of pan.
Pour crushed pineapple over filling.
Add cake mix and pour melted butter over cake mix.
Add nuts and bake at 325° or 350° for 60 minutes.

title: cajun burgers
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into patties. Broil, fry or grill.
Toast buns.
Top each burger with a slice of tomato and
avocado and a dollop of sour cream.
Serves 6.
Preparation time: 30 minutes.
Cooking time: 15 minutes.
Total meal time: 45 minutes.

title: frog-eye salad
directions: Drain canned fruit; reserved 1 3/4 cups pineapple juice. Combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over moderate heat until thick. Add lemon juice and cool.
Bring water, 2 teaspoons salt and oil to a boil.
Add pasta.
Cook at rolling boil until pasta is done, 7 to 9 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and put in baking dish smaller than 13 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: bread and butter pickles(i make mine with zucchini.)
directions: Wash pickles and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Add sliced onions and peppers cut in narrow strips and whole garlic cloves.
Sprinkle the salt over the layers as you work.
Now mix a tray of ice cubes through the pickles.
Put another tray on top.
Let stand for 3 hours.
You may need more ice.
It's the salt ice mixture that makes the pickles especially crisp.
Drain and discard salt water. Divide into two batches.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices.
Heat to dissolve sugar.
Divide and pour over each kettle of pickles. Bring to a boil and ladle into sterilized jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: shoestring chicken salad
directions: Prepare veggies and mix with the chicken.
Mix Cool Whip and mayonnaise together and pour over veggies.
Mix and chill.
Just before serving, add the shoestring potatoes.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Put small amount of oil in skillet.
Cook onion and peppers until soft and brown; set aside.
Brown hamburger meat; drain. Cook noodles; drain.
Mix hamburger meat, onion, peppers, corn and all other ingredients together.
Put in a casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then add Mozzarella cheese and serve.

title: barbecued pork roast
directions: Wash and place roast in large roasting pan.
Pour 2 bottles of barbecue sauce over meat.
Cover with foil and bake 6 hours at 300° basting often.
Remove from oven.
When cool, pull apart and put back in sauce.
Simmer on top of stove to reduce liquid.
Serve as is or with rolls for sandwiches.

title: wendell's depression casserole
directions: Mix flour and sugar together in bowl.
Place about 1 cup of tomatoes into bottom of casserole dish.
Add a layer of potatoes and then onion.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle flour/sugar mixture, salt, and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Continue layering until all ingredients are used.
Finish with tomatoes and dot with butter. Bake in a 350 degree oven for about 45 minutes until potatoes are tender.

title: sauerkrautsalat
directions: Squeeze the sauerkraut.
Cut the onions up.
Cut the pineapple to pieces.
Rasp the apple and the carrot as well.
Finally add the Miracle Whip.
Taste with sugar and pineapple juice.

title: dijon chicken salad
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients. In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, honey, mustard, salt and pepper; mix well. Stir into chicken mixture. Cover and refrigerate until serving. Serve on a lettuce-lined plate. Sprinkle with the almonds. Yield: 6 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix thoroughly with hands.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashion syrup cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add syrup.
Beat eggs real good and add.
Stir in flour.
Add flavoring; beat good.
Pour into a greased square or long pan.
Bake in medium oven (325°) until done but not dry.

title: holiday ribbon ring
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour 1 1/2 cups into 6-cup ring mold.
Chill until set but not firm, about 15 minutes.
Chill remaining gelatin in bowl; gradually blend in 1/3 cup of the sour cream (or yogurt) and spoon over gelatin in mold.
Chill until set but not firm, about 15 minutes.
Repeat same with lime jello.
Chill until firm.

title: taco pie
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain well.
Mix in taco seasoning mix.
Spread in a 10-inch pie plate.
In a mixing bowl, combine milk, Bisquick and eggs; beat until smooth.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 35 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven; bake 8 to 10 minutes, or until bubbly.
Serve in slices with lettuce, tomato, sour cream and salsa.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour and soda together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold beaten egg whites into mixture.
Bake at 350° until done (about 1 hour) in a tube pan.

title: senegalese chicken
directions: Place chicken, broth, onion, celery leaves, curry, salt and pepper in Dutch oven. Cover. Simmer, turning chicken more than halfway through cooking, 45 minutes, until tender and instant-read thermometer inserted in thigh without touching bone reads 180°. Remove chicken to platter. Strain broth into 2-cup measure. Discard solids. Skim fat from liquid. Add milk to broth, if necessary, so broth measures a total of 2 cups. Remove skin and discard. Remove meat from bones. Discard bones. Cut meat into bite-size pieces and place in large bowl. Cook noodles according to directions. Add peas during last 2 minutes of cooking. Drain well.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a deep saucepan, combine milk and rice.
Simmer, over low heat, until rice is done (about 45 minutes).
Mix eggs, canned milk, sugar and cornstarch in a bowl and set aside.
When rice is done, add liquid mixture and vanilla.
Bring back to a boil and remove from heat.
Pour into dish and cool.
Sprinkle cinnamon and/or nutmeg on top.
Serve hot or cold.

title: portuguese meat balls
directions: The day before, you prepare the meat with all the condiments. The day you're cooking, you make the balls.
In a saucepan, you put oil and the onion until onion turns goldish brown, then add the tomato sauce.
Put the stove on low and cook the balls in that sauce.
You cook the spaghetti in a separate saucepan.

title: orange blossom salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine vegetables.

title: "wacky" cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Spray 8-inch square pan with Pam. Preheat oven to 325°.
To dry ingredients, add liquid ingredients. Pour all into pan and cook until center is cooked, but still moist.

title: hot fudge for ice cream
directions: Blend cocoa, cornstarch and sugar.
Add boiling water and stir until smooth.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add butter, vanilla and salt.
Pour over ice cream and enjoy!

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cheese and garlic in a large bowl.
Clean artichokes by cutting off the stem and the tips.
Cleanse artichoke by spreading open each leaf while running under water. Shake water out.
Stuff artichokes with bread crumb mixture
by spreading open and filling each leaf.
Place stuffed artichokes in a large pot; sprinkle olive oil all over artichokes.
Fill pot with approximately 1 inch of water; bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat; cook for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Keep checking water in pot.
Add water when water evaporates. Artichokes are done when outer leaves start breaking off.

title: chili beans
directions: Soak kidney beans for 1/2 hour in hot water; put in large pot. Cook 1 hour in 2 quarts water.
Brown ground beef and drain. Chop onions and bell pepper; add to kidney beans along with meat, chili sauce and salt to taste.
Cook for another hour or until beans are done.

title: basil grilled chicken
directions: Press 3/4 teaspoon pepper into meat.
Combine 1/3 cup melted butter and 1/4 cup basil; stir well.
Brush chicken with mixture. Combine 1/2 cup softened butter, 2 tablespoons basil, Parmesan cheese and seasonings in small bowl.
Beat at low speed until mixture is well blended and smooth.
Set aside.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Chill overnight, if possible.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: In a blender or food processor, blend tomatoes.
Add fine chopped vegetable, garlic, Hawaiian peppers and cilantro.
Add V-8 juice, olive oil, vinegar and salt.
Cover and chill.
Garnish with garlic croutons.

title: peach pie
directions: Put butter in 9 x 13 dish and melt. Mix flour, sugar and milk together. Pour batter over butter. Spoon in peaches and syrup. Cook at 350° until brown on top.

title: crawfish salad
directions: Make party sandwiches or eat on crackers.

title: cheesy shrimp quiche
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix cheese and flour.
Add shrimp and onion to cheese mixture.
Spread in pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour in pie shell.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Top with 1 stick of margarine (melted) mixed with cracker crumbs. Cover whole casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine.
Arrange apples in baking dish. Pour dry mixture over the apples.
Sprinkle water over apples and dry mixture.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes and uncovered until crisp on the top, about 30 more minutes.

title: mamma condon's twenty minute pasta sauce
directions: Put the oil in a saucepan.
Add the tomato sauce right from the can.

Add the garlic powder, onion powder, oregano (tip grind the oregano and basil between the palm of your hand and your thumb for extra flavor, the same holds true for all dried herbs), sweet basil and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for twenty minutes.
The sauce is ready and your guests will think you were in the kitchen all day.
Serve over any pasta with garlic bread and salad.
For the adventuresome, add a little of your favorite wine.

title: recipe for a happy family
directions: Mix thoroughly and sprinkle with awareness.
Bake in a moderate oven of everyday life, using as fuel all the grudges and past unpleasantness.
Cool.
Turn out onto a platter of cheerfulness.
Garnish with tears and laughter.
And in large helpings, serve country and community.

title: economy frosting
directions: Boil flour and milk; let cool.
Add margarine, shortening, sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Spread on warm cake.

title: pepper salisbury steak
directions: Form 3 patties from hamburger. Set aside. Cut up vegetables. Saute vegetables 5 minutes with spices.
Put patties in pan with vegetables on medium heat, covered.
Stir and flip patties.
Pour off excess fat. Remove cover after 20 minutes until meat is browned thoroughly.
Pour in gravy. Stir and simmer 10 minutes. While simmering, cook the noodles according to package directions. Pour steak mixture over noodles. Serves 3.

title: squash pie
directions: Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pie crusts are brown.

title: holland rusk torte
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Add sugar; beat again.
Add rest of ingredients, except Cool Whip and egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into first mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish, greased.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
When cool, spread the Cool Whip on top.

title: "microwave pralines"
directions: Mix cream and brown sugar together in a 4-quart bowl. Microwave on High for 13 minutes (stirring while cooking isn't necessary).
Candy thermometer reading should be 227° (soft-ball stage).
Quickly add pecans and margarine, stirring to mix.
Drop candy by teaspoons onto a sheet of foil.

title: dulce de naranja(orange candy)
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt 1 cup sugar to a rich brown color.
Blend in remaining 2 cups sugar, milk and salt. Bring to a boil; cook, covered, for 3 minutes.
Reduce to low heat; cook, uncovered, without stirring to soft ball stage (230° on candy thermometer).
Cool without stirring to 110°.
Fold in pecans and peels.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 24 pieces.

title: mock souffle
directions: Trim crust from bread and tear bread into small pieces. Butter 9-inch
square
pan
or
casserole.
Make
alternating layers
of bread
and cheese, beginning with bread and ending with cheese. Combine all other ingredients and beat well with a
whip.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Roll in nuts and top with a cherry.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Reduce heat and boil 5 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Add jello, baby food, pineapple and sugar.
Blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: slush
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding ginger ale last; stir well. Freeze to slush stage.
Keeps well; may be used as appetizer or in place of beverages.
Yields 15 servings.

title: frosted orange salad
directions: In bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Stir cold water, bananas, pineapple and marshmallows into gelatin.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan, sprayed with cooking spray.
Refrigerate until firm.
Combine sugar, flour and pineapple juice until smooth.
Bring to boil and cook 2 minutes until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount into egg.
Return to heat. Boil 2 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add cooled filling.
Fold in whip cream.
Spread over gelatin.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.

title: granny naylor's banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line loaf pan with wax paper.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pan.
Cook until lightly brown.

title: kidney bean soup
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer.
If necessary, thicken with flour mixed with water.

title: play dough(for children)
directions: In a heavy aluminum saucepan, mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, water and food coloring.
Cook 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from side of pan.
Knead slightly. Store in an airtight container.

title: durango cottage cheese and vegetable dip(yields 2 cups)
directions: Place cottage cheese in an electric blender container; whirl until smooth.
Spoon into a bowl.
Add green pepper, onion powder, chili powder, garlic powder, cumin, water and vinegar; mix well. Spoon into a serving bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve as a dip with raw vegetables.
Ten calories per tablespoon.
Contains less than 1 gm fat per tablespoon, 1 mg cholesterol and 1 mg sodium per tablespoon.

title: bacon biscuit wedges
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl combine flour, bacon, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or fork until consistency of coarse meal.
Add milk; stir with fork until mixture leaves sides of bowl and forms a soft, moist dough. Turn onto floured surface; gently knead 5 or 6 times or until no longer sticky.
Shape dough into ball.
Place on prepared cookie sheet; flatten into 8-inch circle.
With sharp knife, score top surface into 8 wedges.
Bake at 400° for 21 to 26 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with melted margarine.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Makes 8 biscuit wedges.

title: mexican goulash
directions: In a large saucepan saute the ground beef, green pepper and onion over medium heat.
Add chili powder.
After meat is browned add all other ingredients.
Stir together and simmer over low heat for 15-20 minutes. Serve with cornbread muffins.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork into 1/2-inch squares; boil in water with salt until it turns white.
Remove and fry in margarine until brown.
Combine celery, onion, mushrooms and bamboo shoots; cook in 2 tablespoons of butter for 5 minutes.
Add pineapple; bring to a boil.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook until thickened, then add to other ingredients and place into a covered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice, potatoes, noodles or fettucine.

title: nutty apple butter
directions: In a saucepan, combine applesauce, sugar, spices and butter. Bring to a boil and simmer uncovered over low heat for 2 hours or until thick and dark in color.
Stir in nuts.
Makes 3 cups.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs in half.
Gently scoop out yolk.
Mash yolk and add mayonnaise, slaw sauce and seasonings.
Place mixture back into egg white; smooth.
Top with paprika.

title: texas hash
directions: In 2-quart baking dish, saute onions and green peppers in fat.
Add meat and fry until mixture falls apart.
Add chili powder, salt, pepper and uncooked rice. Pour into baking dish; cover and bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oats and let stand 20 minutes.
Stir in brown sugar, sugar, oil or shortening, eggs and salt.
Mix flour, soda and cinnamon together; add to mixture and stir.
Nuts and coconut may be added, if desired.
Pour into 2 (8 or 9-inch) greased cake pans or 1 (11 x 9-inch) greased pan.

title: betty's chili bean bake
directions: Melt the fat in a large skillet.
Add onions and saute until tender and golden brown, add ground meat, brown lightly.
Add the rest of the ingredients except for the cheese.
With a 2 tined fork (to avoid breaking the beans) stir until blended.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2 qt casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the top and bake in a 325 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerated slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour over slaw and put in refrigerator.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add cream cheese until creamy. Add to warm jello; mix well.
When cool, add Cool Whip.
Spread on top of first layer.
Refrigerate.

title: red, white and green salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower, onion rings, green onions and tomatoes.
Stir together mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Salad will keep for several days. Serves 6 to 8.

title: glazed walnuts
directions: Whip egg
white and water until frothy.
Mix dry ingredients with egg
white.
Put on cookie sheet or pie plates and put in oven for 1/2 hour at 300°.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Salt
and
pepper and flour pork chops.
Brown in small amount of
grease.
Layer
pork chops in casserole dish after browning. Mix
soup
and milk; pour over pork chops.	Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Sift together cake mix and gelatin.
Add remaining ingredients; beat well.
Bake in two 9-inch round well greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Heat cream cheese until it is mixable.
Add remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup of pecans.
Make into a ball.
Roll in pecans and chill overnight.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse the beans and place in a 6-quart Dutch oven. Add water until it is at least 2 inches above the beans.
Allow to soak overnight. Drain. Add 5 cups water and bring to a boil.
Cook over medium heat for about 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally and adding water, as needed.
While beans are cooking, place the sausage pieces in a skillet and cook over medium heat until lightly browned.
When the beans are cooked until fork tender, add the sausage pieces and continue cooking over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Melt the butter in a skillet and saute the celery, onions, and bell pepper until tender.
Add to the beans along with the bay leaves, Essence, and Tabasco.
If needed, add more water to the beans.
Bring to a boil and continue cooking for about 30 minutes longer.
The beans should be very tender and the liquid should have thickened slightly. Remove bay leaves.
Stir in parsley. Serve over rice.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Simmer sausage in 2 cups boiling water for 30 to 45 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, except kidney beans, and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add kidney beans last and heat through.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: orange jello delight
directions: I never cared for cole slaw until I tasted this delicious recipe!

title: hoppin' john(traditional charleston dish for new year's day)
directions: Crumble bacon; add to sauteed onions.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend all soups together with only enough liquid to rinse soup cans.
Arrange chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish.
Pour soups over chicken breasts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serve hot over cooked rice.

title: lime pineapple congealed salad
directions: Pour 1 cup of boiling water over lime jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and blend in with mixer while it's still warm, then add 1 cup of ice.
Stir until melted.
Stir in drained, crushed pineapple.
Let set in refrigerator until mixture begins to congeal.
Remove from fridge and add Cool Whip.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into a large congealed salad mold.
Can be ready to serve in several hours.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Place can of Carnation milk in freezer until crystals begin to form.
Mix lime Jell-O with water.
Place on stove on lowest heat and add marshmallows.
Let melt all or partial as desired.
Do not boil.
Chill.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in seasoned water.
Save broth to cook spaghetti. Debone chicken and cut into small pieces.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Add onion and pepper along with grated cheese to hot spaghetti.
Mix in chicken, Ro-Tel and English peas.
Pour into a large greased casserole dish.
Bake slowly at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crispix cereal snack(great for parites, shower or weddings)
directions: Mix cereal and nuts in a large buttered Tupperware bowl. Combine brown sugar, syrup and butter and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour over the cereal and nuts in large bowl. Stir to coat.
Put into two buttered pans, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn out onto aluminum foil and break apart into pieces.
Cool.
When fully cold, put into ice cream pails and seal.
Ready to use.
Has been shared with many people.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until fork tender; drain.
Add green pepper and onion.
Mix together tomato soup, salad oil, vinegar, prepared mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine all and let stand to marinate several hours or overnight.

title: cajun seafood and noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.

Heat oil in nonstick skillet. Cook bell pepper, onion, parsley, red pepper and garlic 3 minutes, stirring. Stir in flour and tomatoes, breaking up tomatoes. Cook, uncovered, stirring frequently, until mixture boils. Stir in okra, shrimp and crabmeat.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Serve over noodles.

title: best ever fudge
directions: Using a heavy aluminum pan, melt butter; add sugar and milk. Bring to boil and boil hard for 10 minutes, stirring gently. Remove from stove; add chocolate bits and mix until melted.
Add Marshmallow Fluff and mix thoroughly.
Do not beat.
Spread on well-buttered tray and put in refrigerator and cut before it gets hard.
Watch that it doesn't get too hard before you cut.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and lightly flour 12 cup tube pan.
In large bowl, beat sugar and butter until light and fluffy; add vanilla and eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, orange peel, baking powder and salt. Add sour cream; beat well.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate; cool completely.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Stir sugar and cocoa to mix well.
Add the milk and margarine. Bring to a boil on medium-high heat.
Stirring constantly, cook for 90 seconds only.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir to blend well.
Add oats and mix.

title: cheese soup
directions: Put water, celery, onion, carrot and bouillon in saucepan and simmer until tender (about 10 minutes). Mix oil and flour together until smooth. Using wire whip, stir into cooked mixture. Add cheese and stir until all is melted. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: waldorf salad
directions: You may subtract any of the following ingredients to form your own variation.
Combine all ingredients and chill.
Garnish with apple slices.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Wash chicken breasts; pat dry and set aside.
Cut crusts off bread; put in blender to make crumbs.
Prepared bread crumbs may be substituted.
Add cheese and parsley to crumbs and mix well. Melt butter; add garlic, mustard and Worcestershire.
Stir well; cool.
Dip chicken into butter mixture, then coat well with bread crumbs.
Place in buttered casserole.
Drizzle remaining butter mixture over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve immediately.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except macaroni; mix well.
Then add macaroni and mix well.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: zucchini-cheese casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook zucchini in boiling salted water about 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain.
In skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in rice, soup, oregano, salt and garlic powder.
In a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish, arrange half of the zucchini.
Top with the ground beef mixture, cottage cheese and the remaining zucchini.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Uncover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven; bake 2 to 3 minutes more. Makes 8 servings.

title: dill pickles
directions: Scrub cucumbers and pack into jars with garlic and dill flowers.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Combine rolled and fine crumbed graham crackers, sugar, baking powder, salt and raisins. Add vanilla and milk with beaten eggs. Add the dry ingredients.
Dates and nuts may be substituted for the raisins.
Pour batter into an 11 x 7-inch pan that has been lightly buttered. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: In a large glass dish, combine the soy sauce, oil, brown sugar, cooking sherry, ginger and garlic powder; mix well.
Add drumsticks; turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight, turning occasionally.
Drain and discard marinade. Place chicken in a single layer on a foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Yields 6 servings.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: quick cabbage saute
directions: In large skillet, toast pine nuts over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Shake pan constantly to avoid burning; remove and set aside.
In same skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Saute leek until slightly softened, about 2 minutes.
Add carrots and red peppers; saute about 3 more minutes.
Add cabbage; saute until just wilted (approximately 3 minutes).
Add chili paste, soy sauce, sherry, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir to combine.
Bring to boil for 1 minute.
Add pine nuts.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add taco seasoning and sour cream, blending well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch size pan (non-metal).
Top with chopped vegetables.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: jello eggs
directions: Break 1/4-inch hole in the top of the eggs.
Drain the eggs and rinse the shells before submersing them in boiling water for a few seconds.
Then fill them with this mixture.
Dissolve the gelatin powders in one cup boiling water.
Then add 2 cups of cold water. Let gel a bit.
Then pour in different colors to get striped eggs. Then put in fridge until morning.

title: overnight dessert
directions: Place 3/4 cup vanilla wafer or graham cracker crumbs in bottom of ungreased pan (9 x 14-inches).
Melt chocolate with oleo.
Add confectioners sugar, egg yolks, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Put chocolate mixture on top of crumbs. Freeze for 2 hours.
Add ice cream.
Spread evenly on top of chocolate.
Sprinkle top with 3/4 cup vanilla wafers crumbs and freeze.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: deer steaks
directions: Chop onion.
Tenderize steaks by salting and rubbing salt into meat.
Pour Worcestershire sauce onto steaks and put onion on top. Cook and grill in oven at 350°.
Add Worcestershire sauce periodically.

title: best ever oreo dessert
directions: Crush the package of Oreos in small chunks, not fine.
Take 1/2 of the Oreo crumbs and put in a
9 x 13-inch pan.
Then slice the half gallon ice cream and place over the Oreos.
Warm hot fudge slightly, and spread over the ice cream.
Top with remaining Oreo crumbs.
Freeze until firm.

title: beef-onion-mac casserole
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain.
Stir in soup mix, flour, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle and bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6.

title: rice consomme
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir together all ingredients.
Bake in a casserole dish at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken. Line casserole dish with chips and add chicken and onions. Mix chili powder, soup, garlic and tomatoes and pour over other ingredients. Top with cheese and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: roasted quail
directions: Wipe birds with damp cloth.
Rub generously with butter, salt and pepper, inside and out.
Brown in very hot oven, 450° to 500° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; add a little chicken broth and steam 20 to 25 minutes.
The steaming keeps birds moist and helps hold flavor.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: 1st Layer: Prepare broccoli as directed on package. Pour into buttered casserole dish.

title: energy blaster
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high until smooth.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: strawberry sangria ice
directions: In a large bowl crush 1/2 basket of the strawberries with the sugar.
Add wine, lemon juice and orange juice concentrate, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Pour into a shallow pan; freeze until firm.

title: small pecan tarts
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until mixture is melted and well blended.
Fill each pastry shell half full with filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 15 tarts.

title: chess cheese squares
directions: Mix by hand cake mix, egg, and margarine. Spread in 9 x 13 inch pan. Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar, and eggs. Spread on top of cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: bishop bread
directions: Mix 1/4 cup flour with dates and nuts.
Mix all together and bake in loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour.
This is good sliced with cream cheese between slices.
Cut into finger slices.

title: italian style brazzoli
directions: Place meat in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Cover with lid or plastic wrap.
Put in microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Drain. Stir in parsley, salt, basil, pepper, garlic and water; re-cover. Put microwave on simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except spaghetti.
Re-cover and continue cooking on simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until meat is fork-tender.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Serve over spaghetti. Can substitute noodles for spaghetti.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: kidney bean roast
directions: Grind beans and potatoes.
Braise onion, sage and celery leaves.
Add this to beans and potato mixture along with egg, flour and salt.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine bread cubes and butter.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer tomato mixture and bread cubes, ending with bread cubes on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Grease with butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with the tortilla triangles (up the sides, too).
Layer 1/2 of chicken.
Combine chilies, soups (both), onion, olives and milk in large bowl.
Pour 1/2 of soup mixture over chicken layer.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese.
Layer tortillas over the cheese mixture to line completely (including up the sides).
Layer again with chicken, soup and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let sit 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in frying pan.
Add meat and brown quickly. Take meat from pan and set aside.
Add other half of the butter to pan and onion. Cook until clear.
Add mushrooms and flour to make a roux.
Add beef broth, sour cream and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until thick. Add meat.
Mix meat sauce with noodles. Bake in baking dish at 350° for about 1 hour. Sprinkle top with parsley.

title: grandma merritt's sweet potato biscuits
directions: Boil potatoes until they are done or a fork pierces them easily.
Pour cold water over potatoes and remove skin.
Cream potatoes in Crisco.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well with fingers.
If too sticky, add more flour.
Work it up like you would biscuits.
Roll out.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Do not place on lowest rack of oven.

title: chicken elegante
directions: In a large casserole dish, place each chicken breast, wrapped in a slice of dried beef and 1 to 2 strips of bacon.
Spoon soup and sour cream mixture over the chicken.
Place in a 300° oven for 3 hours.
Cover with aluminum foil after cooking.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Mix the first 4 items.
Add zucchini, pineapple, flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, baking powder, nutmeg, raisins and nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and sugar into a mixing bowl. In another bowl, beat the eggs, then beat in the buttermilk. Add the eggs and buttermilk mixture to the flour and mix thoroughly. Add melted butter or oil and beat well. Set aside and allow to stand for at least 1 hour.

title: orange pudding cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients together in saucepan until it all melts.
After removing cake from oven and while it is hot, punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour melted ingredients slowly over cake.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Place
vinegar,
water,
sugar	and
salt
in saucepan. Bring to	a
boil, stirring constantly.
Cool and add mustard seed. Pour
over	chopped
vegetables
that
have
been mixed together in a bowl.	Stir and cover and let stand in refrigerator for 1 day before freezing or leave in refrigerator.
This keeps almost indefinitely.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Place pastry shell on a preheated baking sheet in a 450° oven. Bake at 450° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven to 325°.
In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, flour, onion, parsley, basil, salt, mustard and pepper.
Sprinkle cheese and chicken evenly over the partially baked pastry shell.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake in 325° oven about 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line bottom of a casserole dish with wafers.
Cover with banana slices.
Repeat with alternating layers until casserole is filled.
Set aside.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Place bread crumbs on bottom of buttered casserole dish. Cover with cheese and mushrooms.
Add meat.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over layered mixture.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, pour mushroom soup on casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy cucumber pickles
directions: Combine thinly sliced, unpeeled firm cucumbers. Add diced bell pepper, thinly sliced onion and salt. Add water to cover and let stand for 1 hour. Drain. Mix together the sugar, vinegar and celery seed. Pour over drained cucumbers. Refrigerate in a covered jar or bowl. Let "season" several days.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper.
Remove seeds and membranes.
Rinse.
Cook peppers in enough boiling water to cover for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cook and stir hamburger and onion in skillet until
meat is light brown.
Drain.
Stir in salt, garlic powder, rice and 1 cup of the tomato sauce.
Heat through.

title: potato salad (mrs. mac)
directions: Cut potatoes in small pieces, then cook until done.
Cut onion and celery in small pieces and add potatoes while still hot.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add cut up hard-boiled eggs and add mayonnaise last.
Gently toss and sprinkle with paprika for looks.

title: chicken saute
directions: Slice zucchini 1/8-inch thick.
Bone chicken breasts and cut into bite size pieces.
Put butter in pan until clarified.
Pour in olive oil.
Add chicken, zucchini, garlic, mushrooms, celery, oleo and oregano.
Cover and simmer.
Pour over cooked noodles.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Toss and serve.

title: broccoli-mushroom chowder
directions: Clean and cut broccoli into 1/2-inch pieces.
Steam until tender.
Do not drain.
Set aside.
Wash and slice mushrooms.
Heat butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour to make a roux. Cook for 2 to 4 minutes.
Add chicken stock, stirring with wire whisk and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low.
Add broccoli, mushrooms, half and half cream, salt, pepper and tarragon leaves. Heat but do not boil.

title: spanish bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese. Pour half of mix in dish, layer cheese on it and pour in remainder of mix.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: fried wontons
directions: Heat wok.
Add oil and ground pork.
Cook until meat loses reddish color.
Add shrimp, soy sauce, wine, salt, sliced water chestnuts and green onions.
Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Combine cornstarch and water in separate bowl.
Drain meat mixture on wax paper.
Place approximately 1 teaspoon of filling in center of each wrapper.
Pinch firmly together after putting cornstarch around all edges.
Heat oil to 375°.
Deep fry until crisp and golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm with sweet and sour sauce and hot mustard.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Chop and mix all ingredients together; form ball.
On Shrimp Ball, cover with cocktail sauce.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: one dish ham supper(12 servings)
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and toss with beans and sour cream.
Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Saute onion until tender.
Blend in flour, Worchestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Add cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Divide macaroni mixture between 2 buttered 2 1/2-quart baking pans (shallow).
Pour 1/4 of cheese mixture over each. Arrange ham over macaroni.
Top with remaining cheese sauce. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into loaf. Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly; pack firmly into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing. Makes 8 servings.
tags: cream of mushroom dry soup mix

title: daddy's coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, your evaporated milk, sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla.
This should take about 10 to 12 minutes.
Then add coconut and pecans; beat until thick enough to spread.

title: date delights
directions: Combine date & milk in boiler.
Cook until thick.
Remove and stir in pecans.
Spread on crackers.
Bake 6-7 minutes in 325 degree oven.
Mix cream cheese, butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cooled ritz crackers.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
Mix taco seasoning mix with 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce (reserve remaining sauce); add to beef and cook for 5 minutes.

title: "salmorejo"
directions: Boil the eggs (keep out).
For half an hour, soak the bread in water.
Grind the rest of the ingredients all together.
Squeeze the bread and mix with the ground ingredients.
Serve up cold and with chopped, hard-boiled eggs.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix 2 cups Cheese Nips (crushed) with 1/2 stick melted oleo.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: spanish eggplant and rice
directions: Cook onion and eggplant in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes and cook another 10 minutes.
Add cooked rice.
Then add remaining seasoning and cook another 10 to 15 minutes or desired consistency.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: When cool, mix pudding and pineapple.
Beat until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip and put layers together with mixture and ice cake with remaining mixture.

title: italian cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until creamy. Gradually add baking powder and flour, mixing with your hands as you would bread.
All flour may not be required.
Consistency should not be sticky but easy to work.
Roll dough to form ropes and twist to make desired shapes.
Decorate with candy or icing. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cheese puffs(tiny, savory souffles)
directions: With an inverted drinking glass, cut out 8 rounds of bread (each about 2 inches in diameter) and toast on one side.
Cool, spread untoasted sides with butter.
Combine cheese, baking powder, beaten egg yolk and sprinkling of cayenne pepper and blend thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Spread a thick layer of mix gently on buttered side of toasted rounds, place on a baking sheet.
Broil until puffed-up and browned.
Serve.

title: honey-orange sauce(dressing)
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in blender; process until smooth.
Place yogurt and mixture in a bowl; blend gently.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
(Good served over a fruit salad.)

title: veal marsala
directions: Pound the veal lightly until thin.
Dredge with flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Heat butter; add veal and brown on both sides.
Add Marsala and cook for 1 minute longer over heat. Transfer the meat to warm platter.
Add bouillon to the drippings and bring to a boil, then pour over veal.

title: heath brickle cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream margarine; add sugar, egg and vanilla and mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add Heath brickle and nuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans, onion and ketchup together in a baking dish. Arrange bacon on top and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: michigan blueberry pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 2 cups blueberries with sugar, flour, margarine, lemon juice, nutmeg and salt.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix raisin bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in a large bowl. In a separate bowl, mix eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Combine ingredients together and store in a plastic container in the refrigerator.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together. Fold in fruit.
Pour mixture into baking dish over butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until golden brown.

title: minty roasted potatoes(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prick potatoes with the tines of a fork and arrange them on a baking sheet.
Bake for 1/2 hour.
Cut potatoes into quarters.
Put them in a serving bowl.
While they are hot, toss them with the oil, coarse salt, pepper and garlic. Gently toss in the mint.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise and remove yolks.
Set whites aside.
Mash yolks with a fork, blend in remaining ingredients. Fill each egg half with about 1 tablespoon of yolk mixture. Chill.

title: orange date nut cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and buttermilk; mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When done, stick holes in cake with long-tine fork.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat.
Cook onions in margarine.
Remove from heat and add mushrooms and ketchup.
Mix flour and stock and stir into onions.
Add salt and pepper.
Heat slowly and gradually add sour cream, stirring constantly.
Pour over meat and put in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo (butter) until clarified. Combine all the rest of the ingredients except cheese.
Season to taste.

title: fast fixin' chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into
a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Tilt pan to spread oil all over pan.
Put in remaining ingredients.
Stir with a fork or spoon until blended (about 2 minutes).
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until tested done.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions; cool.
Punch holes in brownies with a fork and pour Kahlua or creme de cacao over brownies; set aside.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Tear cake into small pieces and place in long baking dish. Mix pudding and milk until thickened.
Blend in other ingredients until smooth.
Pour over cake and chill about 4 hours.

title: applesauce buttermilk cake
directions: In medium bowl, stir together flour, cinnamon, soda, nutmeg and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, cream margarine and sugar until light; beat in eggs until well blended.
Stir in applesauce and buttermilk.
Gradually stir in flour mixture until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack.
Serve from pan. Makes 8 servings.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop the popcorn first.
In microwavable mixing bowl, combine butter, syrup and sugar.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes (or until brittle threads form when small amount is dropped into cold water), stirring every 3 minutes.
Combine popcorn and peanuts in large bowl.
Stir vanilla into cooked mixture and immediately pour over popcorn/peanuts.
Stir until evenly coated.
Let cool.
Store in an airtight container.
Enjoy!

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish with little sweet pickles and parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: richard ii eggs
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well. Make white sauce with butter, flour and milk; cook until thickened.
Add minced onion, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce to taste.
Set aside.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Cube cake into mixture and mix gently.
Spread glaze over this. Chill overnight and serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and rinse.
Put back in pan with taco seasoning mix and 1/2 cup of water.
Cook and stir 5 minutes, until thick.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: squash dressing
directions: Drain squash of all liquid.
Mix with other ingredients in buttered 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs (well beaten) and milk. Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to first mixture.
Add graham crackers, coconut and vanilla.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° either in 2 layers or in single layer.
Good served with whipped cream.

title: stay in bed stew
directions: Put in a large casserole and seal with foil all around.
Cook at 275° for 5 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, bananas, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and almonds.
Fold in yogurt.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Dice up and cook chicken; add onions and cook till tender. Add mushrooms and alfredo sauce. Put to the side. Mix together the cottage cheese and ricotta cheese, set aside. In a 9x11 pan, layer lasagna noodles, chicken mixture and ricotta/cottage cheese mix till all is used. Sprinkle with the mozzarella cheese. Bake at 375 for approximate 1 hour, longer if necessary.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake a sheet cake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, pudding mix and milk.
Spread over cake.
Add drained fruit.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Makes one medium size ball, then roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: ham and cheese strata(one dish meal)
directions: Place six slices of bread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cover with 1 cup Cheddar cheese, broccoli, ham and remaining bread slices, cut in half diagonally.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Blend in milk and mustard.
Pour over bread.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
(You may make the night before; hold the milk and egg mixture and add just before baking.)

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans with water 2 times the amount for 4 hrs.
Drain water so it is just covering beans.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook on low or high for 12 hrs.
Do not stir.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat.
Stir in cornstarch, salt and pepper until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Slowly stir in milk until smooth.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute.
Add onion.
Place remaining ingredients in greased 2-quart casserole.
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until heated.

title: chicken velvet soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend
in flour and add milk, light cream and broth.
Cook
and
stir until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.	Reduce	heat.
Stir
in chicken and dash of pepper. Heat again until boiling.
Add optional vegetables (if desired).

title: glorified rice salad
directions: Mix all together, except cream, and let stand 1 hour.
Fold cream in just before serving.

title: bacon fried rice
directions: Refrigerate cooked rice until thoroughly chilled.
Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Drain on paper towels; crumble. Reserve 1/4 cup bacon drippings.
Combine soy sauce and water; set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon bacon drippings in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and red pepper; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add chicken and water chestnuts; stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from skillet; set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon bacon drippings in skillet; add carrots and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add green pepper, celery and onion and stir-fry for 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: frosted party mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Melt chocolate bark in microwave oven or over boiling water.
Stir until smooth.
Pour white chocolate over cereal mixture.
Toss to coat evenly.
Spread mixture on waxed paper to dry.
Break into small chunks.
Store tightly covered.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands.
Shape loosely in small 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
These can be frozen.

title: steam show cookies
directions: Mix all together and bake 8-10 minutes in a 350 degree oven.

title: corn flakes candy
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar then bring to a boil.
Turn off burner.
Add peanut butter and butter.
Pour over corn flakes. Use a plastic spoon to glob onto wax paper.
Store in a plastic container.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and Wesson oil.
Sift flour, soda and salt. Add to sugar mixture.
Add red food coloring and milk.
Mix vanilla, vinegar and cocoa.
Add to batter.
Pour into greased and floured single cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Rub a 2-quart dish with butter. Mix all ingredients well and pour into casserole. Top with buttery crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Place bacon on roasting rack.
Microwave at High until crisp, 5 to 6 minutes.
Crumble and set aside.
Combine eggs, half and half, green onion, flour, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper in medium bowl.
Beat with a wire whisk or electric mixer until blended.
Microwave at Medium until thoroughly heated and slightly thickened.
Put bacon in pastry shell.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Put hot egg mixture over cheese.
Microwave at Medium until center is set but not dry, 16 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onions in 1/2 margarine.
Add broccoli (precooked) and simmer until tender.
Add rest of margarine and other ingredients. Serve hot with corn chips.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Before making sauce, break cake into small pieces and put on bottom of pan or Pyrex dish.
Melt butter; let cool.
Mix butter with egg yolks, powdered sugar and Cool Whip (1 small).
Pour sauce over cake layer (on bottom of pan).
Layer crushed Butterfingers over sauce layer.
Top with Cool Whip (1 small).
Seal edges.
Can add shaven chocolate, if desired.
Serves approximately 15 to 20. Preparation Time:
20 to 25 minutes.
Delicious!

title: bulldog cookies
directions: Into empty dishwashing detergent bottle (22 ounce size), fill 1/3 full with 10% iodine.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of Dawn dishwashing detergent.
Fill rest of bottle with water.
Shampoo dogs.
Be sure to rinse well.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With wire whisk, beat eggs well. Beat in next
five
ingredients	until
well blended.
Arrange pecan halves on
bottom of crust.
Slowly pour pumpkin mixture over pecans.
Bake 1
hour or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Let cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove tops of peppers; wash, clean and parboil.
Crumble and brown beef, sauteing onion at the same time.
Pour off any grease that accumulates, then add rice, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, mustard, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir to blend well. Cover and cook about 20 minutes over low heat.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
(Optional: Pour can of tomatoes over top of peppers). Top peppers with grated cheese and bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal pies
directions: Mix everything together very well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: fluffy orange cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar with electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or 12 cup fluted tube pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan. Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.
Makes 12 servings. Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cooking Time:
40 minutes standing.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Put macaroni in large bowl.
Let margarine melt on its own on top of macaroni.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put in baking dish and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Can cut recipe in half.

title: light chicken spaghetti
directions: Coat a large skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add diced onion, celery, green pepper and minced garlic; saute until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, paprika, chili powder, cumin, pepper and red pepper.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add chicken, cover and simmer 15 minutes. Serve chicken over hot spaghetti.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with the chopped rhubarb. Sprinkle the 3/4 to 1 cup sugar and the cinnamon.
Mix the other ingredients and spread over rhubarb; it will be thick.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry nut pound cake
directions: Combine oleo and sugar; beat well.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla and mix in flour gradually.
Fold in cherries and nuts.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans; pour batter in.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center and add oil, egg yolks, oil and water.
Beat until smooth. Set aside.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until very stiff and able to be cut with a knife. Pour egg yolk mixture over whipped egg whites and fold in gently. Do not stir.
Bake in three 8-inch layer pans lined with waxed paper at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mccullough's short ribs, crock-pot style
directions: Place thawed short ribs in crock-pot.
Add brown sugar, mustard and butter.
Add margarine.
Set on low and cook for 10 hours.
Serve with peas and mashed potatoes.
Delicious.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: The night before, layer bread, sausage and grated cheese in a buttered baking dish. Combine eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard and pour over the ingredients in the baking dish. Refrigerate overnight. In the morning, bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 12 to 14.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy, then add sugar and baking powder gradually.
Continue beating until whites are stiff.
Fold in crackers, nuts, salt and vanilla.
Bake in well-buttered 9-inch pie plate at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, ice cream and strawberries or ice cream and hot fudge sauce.

title: chocolate rum cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 2 (8-inch) cake layer pans.
When cool, cut both layers in half, using thread to make 4 layers.
Make pudding, using only 1 1/2 cups milk.
Remove from heat; let cool some.
Add 1/4 cup rum; let cool completely.
Whip the cream; add 1/2 cup to pudding.
Fold in.
Set rest of whipped cream aside.
Put pudding mixture between layers.
To the remaining whipped cream, add the confectioners sugar and 1 tablespoon rum.
Ice outside of cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in a large bowl.
Blend well (just stir with a spoon, no need using a mixer). Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Do not beat.
Stir in nuts.

title: chocolate fudgesicles
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine pudding, sugar and milk. Pour mixture into small plastic cups or popsicle molds and freeze. When the
popsicles have set, insert a popsicle stick into each one. Serve when frozen.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake through until cooked, about 20 minutes.
Cool chicken and cut into bite sized pieces.

title: banana split cake
directions: Spread graham cracker crumbs and butter mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup butter, eggs, vanilla and confectioners sugar; beat until fluffy and custard like.
Spread over graham cracker mixture.
Spread bananas and drained pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with walnuts and cherries.
Drizzle chocolate syrup on top.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: tabouli(wheat garden salad)
directions: In medium bowl, pour boiling water over bulgur wheat.
Let sit 1/2 hour.
In shaker, combine oil, lemon juice, garlic, salt, oregano, basil and cayenne; shake well.
Mix wheat and vegetables well.
Pour in oil mixture.
Mix well.
Chill for several hours. Serve on a bed of lettuce.
Yields ten 1/2 cup servings.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Stir in seasonings.
Add tomatoes, mushroom soup and rice.
Mix well.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese.
Replace top and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Takes 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Chop all ingredients and mix together; pepper to taste.
Mix in 3/4 cup Miracle whip.
Best if fixed 24 hours in advance of use.

title: chicken strata
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer bread, cheese and chicken.
End with bread.
Sprinkle with onion flakes.
In a bowl, beat eggs, milk, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pour over top of layers and sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cover with soup or serve soup on the side.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add strawberries, stirring until thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Serve on lettuce ruffle.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low heat for 8 to 12 hours or on high for 2 to 3 hours.

title: baked chili relleno
directions: Put peppers in 7 x 11-inch baking pan.
Cover with grated cheese.
Beat eggs; add flour, milk and salt.
Pour over cheese. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° until custard sets.

title: eileen's baked apple squares
directions: In a large bowl, beat together sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add oil and vanilla and mix thoroughly. Fold in apples.
Add nuts, if using.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: lemon sugar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Put in a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool cake for 20 minutes, then prick the top all over with a fork.
Thoroughly mix the lemon juice and powdered sugar, then spoon all over the top of the cake.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and shape into ball.
Roll in pecans, if desired. Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until frosty.
Add sugar; stir in butter and then add all the other ingredients.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Bake pie for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Add eggs and fruit (juice and all).
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 300° about 1 hour or until done.

title: baked creole eggplant
directions: Boil eggplant until soft.
Saute onion, shrimp and celery in butter.
Combine with eggplant.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: toffee - microwave
directions: Rub top of bowl with butter.
Place butter in bowl.
Pour sugar on butter.
Add salt and water.
Cook for 7 to 8 minutes. Don't stir.
Do not overcook.
Done when it gets a light brown toffee color.
Pour over almonds that have been spread on small buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.
Melt chocolate bar in microwave. Spread on candy.
Sprinkle crushed almonds on top of chocolate. Cool.

title: chris's homemade salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for about 30 minutes.
Serve over eggplant parmesan.

title: light soup
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Cut up potatoes in large pot.
Add tomatoes, sweet peas, green peppers and onion.
Salt to taste. Cook until potatoes are done over medium heat.
Great diet soup! Low in fat.

title: sauteed chicken breasts
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour and pepper.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.
In skillet in hot oil cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove and set aside.
Spoon off fat.
In skillet combine soup and water, heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet, cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring often.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: finger jello
directions: In a large bowl, combine gelatines and boiling water; pour into shallow baking pan (13 x 9-inch).
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.
Makes about 100 (1-inch) squares.

title: potato latkes
directions: Grate potatoes and drain well.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Drop from a spoon into hot oil and brown on both sides.

title: mincemeat squares(can do ahead.  can freeze.)
directions: Combine oatmeal, flour and brown sugar; mix thoroughly.
Cut in the butter until mixture is crumbly.
Divide into 2 parts. Place one-half firmly in the bottom of a greased 12 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: kay's chicken vegetable soup
directions: Cook chicken 1 1/2 hours in water.
Save broth.
Take chicken off bone and put back in broth.
Place in bowl and put into refrigerator overnight.
Skim off fat.
Put in large pan and add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook about 1 to 2 hours.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: garlic bread
directions: Spread each half of bread liberally with butter or margarine. Sprinkle with Garlic Bread Sprinkle.
Place in 350° oven set to bake; do not use pan or foil.
Place directly on rack.
Bake 10 minutes until butter is melted and bread is thoroughly hot. Change setting to broil and watch closely as bread browns.
It is easy to burn.
Slice and serve hot.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake in oven for about 3 hours.
Cover top with small chips of bacon if preferred.
Bake at 250° to 300°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, chill, serve with your choice of fresh vegetables.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, then crumble.
Wash and cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Combine in a bowl the broccoli, bacon, raisins and chopped onion.
In another bowl, mix well the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour dressing over salad; toss and refrigerate.
A very appealing salad that can be made 3 to 4 hours ahead of time.

title: nacho dip
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan, spread mixture of beans, taco seasoning and taco sauce.
Start layering remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Chill and serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: potato au gratin
directions: Boil diced potatoes until barely done; drain while warm. Season immediately; layer potatoes, soup mixed with milk, bell pepper and cubed cheese.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chili
