directions: Brown hamburger and onion, no need to drain if you use extra lean meat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 1 to 2 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage at room temperature.
Knead flour and sausage together.
Add cheese and mix together.
Make into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot.
Can be frozen and baked later.

title: scramble
directions: Mix in very large baking pan. Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes. (This recipe makes a lot of Scramble!)

title: quick meat loaf
directions: Mix together and make into loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour cookie sheet pan.
Mix cake mix per directions.
Bake 15 minutes only.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fold into a round cake pan (also works well in a bread pan).
Freeze.
When ready to serve, let stand for a few minutes and cut into slices.

title: creamed corn
directions: In a saucepan, melt the butter, add chopped onion and saute for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until onion is done.
Add the corn and cook for 5 minutes.
Add the jalapenos and stir into the corn mixture.
Stir in the cream cheese.
Cook over low heat until the cream cheese has melted and the corn kernels are coated in the mixture.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: hot sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Add can enchilada sauce and can of jalapeno relish.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer until thick.
Serve in bowls, using chips to dip into to eat.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Split muffins and toast until lightly browned.
Top each muffin half with a tomato slice.
Combine beef, catsup, onion salt, oregano and basil.
Spread mixture over tomato.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 3 minutes.
Top with cheese strips; broil 1 more minute.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: creamy swiss green beans
directions: Cook onion in 2 Tbsp. of the butter, till tender.
Stir in flour, salt, and milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Drain beans, stir into sauce with sour cream and cheese. Pour into baking dish.
Melt remaining butter and mix with crumbs. Sprinkle over beans.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20-25 minutes.

title: quick spaghetti
directions: Cook the macaroni and cheese as per the instructions on its box and set aside.
Cook the ground beef in a skillet (seasoning is optional).
Mix the cooked ground beef, the jar of Prego sauce and water with the macaroni and cheese.
Let simmer on low for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese and dill pickles
directions: Form a thick coating of cream cheese around the pickle, covering the ends.
Wrap a slice of ham around each pickle and slice into rounds.

title: carolina deviled seafood
directions: Prepare all seafood; cook until tender, adding oysters afterwards.
Cut up vegetables; cook the celery, onion and pepper until tender and add to seafood with the mashed potatoes, red pepper, salt and Worcestershire to taste.

Add 1 or 2 eggs with sufficient cracker crumbs to make right consistency to fill ramekins or shells which have been greased with a little butter. After filling, sprinkle with cracker crumbs and dot with butter. Bake for about 10 minutes in a hot oven.
Serve with lemon as a garnish.
Serves 8.

title: refrigerator lemon pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour into pie crusts.
Refrigerate until set, about 6 to 8 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crust and egg whites, in heavy saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring constantly (spoon with holes works best).
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell. Use saved egg whites to make meringue topping, if desired.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, put mixture into pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, cool down and refrigerate.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Layer in baking dish:
eggplant, sauce and cheese.
Take milk and flour, make into a white sauce and pour on top.
End with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together with hands; roll into small balls.
Place onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° to 300° until done and brown, about 15 minutes.
Keep turning.

title: spinach lasagne noodles
directions: Boil and drain spinach well; put through blender.
Make flour into mound on table and scoop out a well.
Place strained, blended spinach, eggs and salt into well of flour.
Work into flour.
Knead thoroughly.
If necessary, add more flour.
Divide kneaded dough into 2 parts and roll out very thin.
Stretch dough on clean dry towels.
Let dry 1 hour.
Fold each sheet and cut across dough into lasagne noodles.
Can use regular filling on noodles, boiled very slightly.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix together and allow to marinate overnight.

title: mousse in a minute
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on the package using 1 1/2 cups milk.
Fold in the Cool Whip if desired.
Makes 2 2/3 cups or 5 servings.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown meat and green pepper.
Drain excess fat.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour or more in crock-pot.
Serve with king size corn chips.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.

title: quickie beef stew
directions: Drain vegetables.
Reserve liquid.
Combine flour and soup mix in large skillet.
Add water to reserved liquid to measure 3 cups. Stir into mixture in skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Stir constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add vegetables and beef.
Cover.
Cook over low heat about 10 minutes.
Yields 4 servings, about 1 1/2 cups each.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as instructed on box in a sheet pan.
Cook as directed.
Mix sour cream and sugar together.
When cake comes from oven, punch small holes and put mixture on the cake. Sprinkle fresh coconut or 2 packages of frozen coconut.
(I use frozen coconut.)
While hot, wrap cake with Reynolds Wrap and put back in oven overnight (oven to be turned off).
Put cake in refrigerator next morning.

title: butter crescents
directions: Scald milk
and pour over butter, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle
yeast on warm water; stir to dissolve. Add egg, yeast	and
2	cups flour to milk mixture.
Beat with mixer at	low
speed
until
smooth,
about 1 minute.
Beat at medium speed until thick, about 2 minutes.
Add enough remaining flour and mix with spoon until dough leaves sides of bowl. Turn onto lightly
floured
board and knead gently.
Put into greased bowl and
invert
to grease top of dough.
Cover with clean towel
and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Turn
dough onto
board; divide in half; cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Roll each half to make a 12-inch circle; cut each circle in
12 wedges.
Roll
up each wedge from wide end and put pointed end down on greased baking sheets (you'll need 2).
Curve ends slightly to make crescents.
Cover with towel. Let rise
until doubled,
about 30 minutes.
Bake in hot 400° oven for 15 minutes. Makes 24 crescents.

title: barbecue pork in buns
directions: Twenty minutes before serving, in a 12-inch skillet over medium high heat, in hot salad oil, cook pork until well browned, turning once.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
With tongs, place cutlets in buns.
Keep warm.
Reduce heat to medium.
Into drippings in skillet, stir ketchup, molasses and lemon juice. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Spoon some sauce over meat in each bun.
Makes 6 servings.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring water, oleo and cocoa to a boil, stirring to prevent lumps.
Cool slightly, then pour over flour, sugar, salt and soda that have been sifted together.
Combine eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Add to chocolate mixture and mix well.
Bake in an 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: "company corn"
directions: Roast for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool and fill in freezer containers.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and
pour into well-greased pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Use 8 x 12-inch pan for baking.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Cook sausage until done, stirring to crumble.
Drain well on paper towels.
Combine sausage and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: filling for pirohi
directions: Drain cottage cheese.
Combine ingredients and mix until smooth.

title: hidden valley oyster crackers
directions: Combine oil and dressing mix.
Add spices.
Pour over crackers.
Stir to coat.
Place in warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes on cookie sheet or microwave on low for 5 minutes.

title: philadelphia "phudge"
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together over low heat (or in microwave); stir until smooth.
Beat cream cheese in bowl with mixer until fluffy.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla and salt; beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread into 8-inch square pan, lined with foil.
Chill until firm, then cut into squares.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in drippings until crisp-tender.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to make mixture equal 1 3/4 cups.
Chop tomatoes.
Add tomatoes, tomato liquid, tomato sauce and next 3 ingredients to onion mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir rice; sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes. Sprinkle with bacon.
Serves 6.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter an 8-inch square pan very well. Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Beat egg and milk together; add corn and mix well.
Saute onion, chiles and pimiento in butter in skillet until onion is tender.
Add milk mixture, onion mixture and cheese to dry ingredients.
Stir just until mixed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: the all american dessert
directions: Stir 2 cups boiling water into 2 bowls until Jell-O is completely dissolved.
Stir 1 cup cold water into each bowl.
Pour into separate 13 x 9-inch pans.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Layer red and blue Jell-O, Cool Whip, blueberries, cake cubes and strawberries in 3-quart clear bowl. Chill 1 hour and serve.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Wrap diced apples in a crescent roll, 1 at a time. Grease dish (9 x 13 casserole). Put layer of rolls in casserole dish. Pour sauce over rolls. Bake 30 minutes at 350°; if not brown, bake a little longer. Dip sauce over rolls all during baking time.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together and add buttermilk to make soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured bread board.
Knead lightly.
Roll or pat out dough to thickness of 1/4 in.
Cut into squares of 2 -3 in and slit center of each square.
Drop into hot oil: brown on both sides.
Serve hot with honey or taco fixings.

title: hot sesame-cheese rolled sandwiches
directions: Use a rolling pin to flatten slices of bread.
Spread each with cheese; sprinkle with sesame seed.
Roll each slice jelly roll fashion; brush with melted butter.
Cover with waxed paper or plastic wrap; chill several hours.
Cut rolls in half crosswise and place on baking sheet, seam side down.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
32 small sandwiches.

title: chewy fudge squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together, then bake 28 minutes.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Add cold water to liquid to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid. Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened (consistency of unbeaten egg whites).

title: low calorie pastiere
directions: In a bowl, beat the eggs well.
Add the cottage cheese, grated cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Gently toss the macaroni into the mixture.
Generously grease an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add the macaroni mixture.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Brown hominy and onion in fat, add other ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes, until hominy is tender and gravy heavy.

title: chicken dressing and gravy(serves 8)
directions: Cook chicken, debone and save broth.
Crumble cornbread and bread.
Add onion.
Mix with soup, broth and milk if needed.
Add eggs; mix well.
Dot dressing with margarine.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.
You can use broiler pan or 2 smaller pans and freeze one for later use.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour melted butter over stuffing mix; set aside.
Combine all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in half of the stuffing mix; toss to mix.
Spread vegetable mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle the remaining half of the stuffing mixture on top.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: snitz and knepp
directions: Wash and soak snitz overnight.
Add water to ham and cook 3 to 4 hours, until almost done.
Add snitz and boil about an hour. Add brown sugar.

title: special carrot cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon in mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat at medium speed 1 minute.
Stir in carrots, nuts, pineapple and coconut.
Bake in three greased 9-inch pans at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Cool on racks.
Fill layers, top and sides with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Stir in rice, onion flakes, salt, water and soup.
Place chicken breasts over top of mixture. Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: scripture cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heavily grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
In a large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter until smooth.
At low speed, add sugar and honey; mix well.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and all of the spices together in a separate bowl.
Add eggs to mixture, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients to batter alternately with buttermilk.
Gently fold in fruit and nuts into batter.
Pour batter in pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick test comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, margarine, celery salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add radishes and green onions last. Chill several hours to blend flavors.

title: no-bake strawberry cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer on high until well blended. Gently stir in Cool Whip, spoon into crust. Refrigerate 3 hours or until set. Top with strawberries just prior to serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: lasagna dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in quiche or pie pan.
Brown hamburger and add Ragu.
Layer over cream cheese.
Pour grated mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake 350 for 30 minutes.
Serve with bread sticks.

title: *strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients. Combine jam and sour cream and add to egg mixture, alternating with dry ingredients until well mixed.
Stir in nuts.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in bananas and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and finally the nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in loaf pan.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack before slicing.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve the jello and sugar in the hot water.
Cool. Add the frozen lemonade and pineapple juice. Freeze. When ready to serve, pour the ginger ale over it.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: *Can use all-purpose flour and 1/2 teaspoon baking powder.

title: irish stew
directions: Put the oil in a large boiler.	Put the diced onion and garlic in boiler.
Let fry in oil until onion is clear.
Pour the tomato sauce and Ro-Tel tomatoes in with onion and garlic. Add
about
cups of water.
If you want more soup, add water.
Let
this cook over medium heat for about 15 minutes. Then
add
potatoes. Cook until potatoes are tender.
Cut off fire.
Add
the
corned beef and let it dissolve in the soup. Let it stand for about 15 minutes before serving.

title: cheese spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing.
Mix until well blended. Add the other ingredients and mix. Chill.
To mold, put around a glass. Drop by teaspoon.
Chill before molding. Sprinkle parsley flakes on top. Serve with crackers.

title: unique cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by spoonful.
Bake for 15 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Could add nuts, raisins, chocolate chips, etc.

title: wimp dip
directions: Drain tomatoes well and put into saucepan.
Chop and add Velveeta until melted and warmed through.
Serve warm with taco chips.
Not very hot!

title: basting sauce for barbecue ribs or chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool slightly, then baste barbecue while sauce is warm.

title: my dad's barbecue beans
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add pork and beans and barbecue sauce. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with salad.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of partially cooked bacon. In bottom of flat casserole (8 x 12-inch), sprinkle a base of beef. Place chicken on beef. Mix soup and sour cream and pour over all. Bake for 3 hours at 275°. Do not let it dry out. Slivered almonds may be sprinkled over top before baking. You may substitute mushroom soup instead of chicken soup.

title: apple butter
directions: Fill large crock-pot full of apples, peeled and cut up.
Cook 4 1/2 hours on high, then 4 hours on low.
Turn off (unplug).
With electric mixer, make sure there are no lumps and smooth.
Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa with milk in double boiler.
Dot margarine in there.
Simmer until mixture starts bubbling.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour out on waxed paper.
Refrigerate for about 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Stir in oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt onto wax paper.
Stir into egg mix until well blended; stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased 8 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pans.
Bake in 375 oven for 1 hour.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove.
Cool completely.

title: hummus
directions: Place the beans and 1/4 cup of the lemon juice in a food processor and process until the beans are mashed but not completely pureed.
Add the garlic, the remaining lemon juice and the tahini and process until the mixture is a smooth puree.
With short on and off pulses, add water to thin out the hummus if it seems too thick.
Season to taste with salt.
To serve, spoon the hummus into a shallow bowl or a rimmed plate.
Drizzle it with olive oil and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve slightly chilled with warmed pita triangles.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In a large bowl, make stiff batter of all ingredients.
Grease another large bowl and put batter in it.
Turn dough over so oily side is up.
Cover lightly with foil and let stand overnight.
Do not refrigerate.
Let rise 10 to 12 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Boil eggs.
Cover bottom of greased casserole dish with cracker crumbs.
Drain asparagus.
Add layer over crumbs.
Add layer of sliced boiled egg and slice of American cheese over egg. Add another layer of same.
Pour over a can of cream of mushroom soup.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over and pour milk on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange coffee cake
directions: Separate biscuits and put cube of cream cheese inside each. Pinch edges of biscuits together.
Dip into melted butter, then dip into sugar/nut mixture.
Stand up in greased Bundt pan.
Pour rest of melted butter over top.
Sprinkle rest of sugar and chopped nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Turn onto plate.
Pour mixture of powdered sugar and orange juice over top and serve.

title: 100 good cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Makes 100 plus good cookies.

title: oatmeal caramel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine oats, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and egg. Mix well. Cut in margarine until crumbly. Stir in nuts.
Reserving 2 cups of crumb mixture, press remainder in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: german dish
directions: Melt butter in large skillet. Add onion; cook until tender. Add apple, brown sugar, potatoes and sauerkraut; mix well. Place sausage on top of sauerkraut mixture. Cover and cook on medium-low heat 30 minutes. Serve hot. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine crab meat and celery. Season to taste. Serve with French dressing.
Garnish with pimiento.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute.
Stirring constantly, gradually add milk, half and half and chicken broth.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in salt, garlic powder, basil and broccoli.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.

title: barbecue meatball
directions: Combine
together
first
ingredients and shape into balls. Take
the	catsup,
onion, bell pepper, sugar, vinegar and water, combine
and pour over balls; then bake at 475° for 45 minutes. Serve over rice or hors d'oeuvres.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Brown hamburger with onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Mix in baking pan with spaghetti.
Add mushrooms, if desired.
Mix well.
Add sauce to desired moisture level.

title: ritz cracker toppings
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and pour over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased casserole after pouring soup over chicken mixture at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: chris' spaghetti sauce
directions: Place oil in heavy pan over heat; add chopped onion and pepper and saute until 1/2 cooked without browning.
Add ground beef and cook until it starts to brown.
Add paste and sauce; stir and let cook until grease has turned red.
Add water and seasoning.
When mixture starts to boil, lower heat to simmer and cook for not less than 5 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookies thin and place on pizza pan (overlap).
Bake until brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Spread on cookies.
Arrange fruit on top.
Dribble preserves over all.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, onion and seasonings.
Simmer 1 hour at least.
Put small amount of sauce on bottom of baking dish.
Layer with cooked noodles, cheese, cottage cheese, Parmesan, the sauce, then start with noodles again.
Top layer should be the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: chili rellenos appetizers
directions: In a lightly greased 9-inch square pan, make layers of chilies and the cheeses, starting and ending with cheeses.
Beat eggs, milk and flour together.
Pour over layered ingredients and bake at 375° about 1 hour or until firm.
Cut into small squares and serve warm. These come out fairly flat and can be picked up with fingers. Makes 16.

title: baked wieners
directions: Slowly simmer all ingredients, except wieners, for 30 minutes. Put slightly cooked wieners in casserole.
Pour sauce over them. Bake 45 minutes in slow oven at 350°.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Spread 1/2 of the cubed bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread cubed cream cheese on top of bread.
Put the rest of the bread on top of the cream cheese.
Mix together milk, eggs and maple syrup and pour over top of bread mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with maple syrup, powdered sugar or fruit.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour, soda and salt. Add oatmeal.

title: easy artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix with mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: charlotte rousse
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar; beat together.
Bring milk to barely boil.
Stir into egg mix gradually, stirring until 1/2 of the milk is used.
Pour this into remaining milk.
Stir over low heat until custard coats a silver spoon.
Strain.
Gelatin should be soaking in 1/4 cup water.
Set cup down in shallow pan of hot water until gelatin is liquid.
Fold gelatin into custard.
Let mixture cool and congeal.
Fold into 1 pint whipped cream that has been whipped (not too stiff).
Flavor with vanilla, bourbon, brandy or your preference.
May be served from large bowl or in compotes lined with ladyfingers.

title: chicken copenhagen
directions: Butter large baking dish, put rice and water in bottom of dish, layer chicken over rice.
Spoon the 3 cans of soup over chicken, dot with butter, add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle cayenne sparingly.
Sprinkle toasted almonds over all.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty foil, bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: museum quilter's tea
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar and shake to mix.
Store in covered jar.
If using sweetened instant tea, omit sugar.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken seasoned with salt, pepper and celery.
Remove from bone and save 1 1/2 quarts of the broth.
Saute the onion and bell pepper in the margarine.
Set aside.
Cook the vermicelli in the chicken broth and do not drain.
When tender, add peas (drained), mushrooms (drained), cheese (cut in small pieces) and Ro-Tel (chopped).
Add onion and bell pepper, then chicken.
Mix carefully.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grilled beef salad - yum nuah(servings:  12)
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together (food processor or blender works well).
This dressing is better if refrigerated for 3 or 4 hours.
Remaining ingredients should be tossed together in large salad bowl.
Add dressing when ready to serve.

title: mallow white cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening with sugar and vanilla until fluffy.

Add sifted dry ingredients and water alternately in thirds, mixing well after each addition. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry, and fold into batter. Pour into greased pans and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 (8-inch) layers.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Stir well and add peanut butter. Cook on High setting for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave; stir well and cook for 1 minute.
Spray a 9-inch square dish with cooking oil.
Line bottom with wax paper and spray with oil. Spread fudge mixture in dish and allow to get firm.
Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: arroz blanco(white rice)
directions: Wash rice.
In a large skillet, add butter and rice.
Cook just until rice changes color; do not brown rice.
Add water, cilantro, jalapeno and onion.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes on low heat.
During last 5 to 10 minutes of cooking, add the cheese and corn.
This dish is done when cheese is melted and corn is heated through.

title: cocktail sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, biscuit mix and cheese. Shape into small meatballs.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 300° for about 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: cream pecan fudge
directions: Melt over low heat the chocolate and milk, then add sugar, corn syrup and flour.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Set out to cool, then put in vanilla, baking powder and nuts.
Beat until it thickens.
Pour into greased pan.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: Sift flour, spices and soda together. Stir brown sugar into melted shortening. Beat well. Add dry ingredients and hot water alternately in small amounts. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Makes one 10 x 10-inch cake.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Place pineapple in baking dish.
Add grated cheese.
Mix juice, flour, sugar and margarine.
Pour over pineapple and cheese.
Top with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until set.

title: french toast kountree kampinn style
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread and mix well.
Dip bread in mixture, turn over and coat both sides.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in large skillet or griddle.
Place one layer of bread slices and fry to golden brown.
Turn and brown.
Serve with butter and syrup.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Combine cornbread mix with other ingredients in a large bowl. Pour into a
greased
Pyrex dish and cook 45 minutes at 350° or until top is puffy and light brown.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight in refrigerator. Serve on crackers.

title: oatmeal crunch cookies
directions: Mix together and roll in balls.
Dip top of cookies in sugar. Bake in 350° oven until nicely brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour 1 cup sugar over diced peaches; set aside. Mix flour, sugar and milk and beat until smooth. Melt butter in casserole dish. Pour batter mix over butter and top with peaches. Spread evenly. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: lemon frozen dessert
directions: Combine last 2 ingredients to make crust crumbs.
Cook beaten egg yolks, sugar, lemon juice and rind.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool well.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites. Fold in whipped cream.
Layer crumb crust with a layer of lemon filling, layer of crumbs and remaining lemon filling.
Save a few crumbs to decorate the top.
Freeze.
May be made well ahead of use.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: In blender, mix all ingredients until it foams. Serve in champagne glasses. Makes 6 large drinks.

title: fresh rabbit
directions: Mix egg and milk in a bowl.
Dip rabbit well and then coat rabbit with flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Place rabbit in hot skillet with hot fat or oil.
Sprinkle with onion.
Sprinkle garlic powder on all sides as you are browning rabbit.
After your rabbit has browned good, remove rabbit.
Place in oven dish or pan.
Drain oil from skillet and return skillet to heat.
Place 2 tablespoons of sour cream in skillet and stir until brown, then add mushroom soup to sour cream in skillet; blend good.
Pour mixture over rabbit, coating well.
Cover rabbit and place in hot oven
at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Ummm good!

title: deviled crab
directions: Mix well.
Place patties of crabmeat on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown, not more than 1/2 hour.

title: a quick, easy, nourishing supper
directions: Fry sliced onions.
When onions are partially done, put chopepd meat in same pan, break up into small pieces and fry until done.
Add soup and V-8 juice.
Simmer a few minutes and it's ready.
Serves 5 or more.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.
Cook at 450° for 15 minutes; then 350° until done, about 10 minutes.

title: macaroni and eggs
directions: Cook the macaroni in 4 quarts salted water, 7 to 10 minutes. Remove from the heat; drain.
Stir in the margarine.
Pour into casserole dish. Beat eggs well. Pour over the macaroni. Bake in a moderate oven for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: double quick coffee cake
directions: Measure into bowl the warm water.
Add and stir to dissolve, yeast.
Stir in sugar, salt and half of 2 1/4 cups flour.
Beat until mixture sheets off spoon (2 minutes).
Add and beat until smooth, 1 egg, remaining flour and 1/4 cup soft shortening.
Drop by spoonfuls over topping.
Cover and let rise in warm place 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn over immediately.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Mix remaining sugar with flour and butter until crumbly; set aside.
Arrange apples on crust and cover with cinnamon mixture; top with crumbly mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, then lower heat to 350° and bake about 40 minutes or until done.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix margarine and cheese. Add flour. Use cookie press for desired shape. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 50.

title: date bars
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients like pie crust.
Put half of mixture in greased pan.
Cook dates, brown sugar, milk and vanilla until thick.
Pour over crumb mixture and top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: curried stew beef and dumplings
directions: Bring water to a boil in kettle or pot.
Season meat with powdered seasonings by rubbing them into meat with hands.
Set aside.
Cut, chop or dice solid seasonings; set aside.
Make dumplings by mixing flour, a little salt and enough water to make doughy and kneadable without sticking.
(If sticky, add flour.
If dry, add water.)
Pinch small portions of dough and roll into balls or longer cylinder pieces; set aside.
Cover bottom of pot with oil; heat and add seasoned meat.
Shake some soy sauce on meat.
After color changes, add some tomato paste and allow to boil.
Add carrots, 3 or 4 bay leaves and enough boiling water to cover ingredients.
Add dumplings and drained potatoes.
Let stew until done.

title: shrimp creole
directions: First, cook rice according to package directions.
Pour oil in large skillet, then put onions, bell peppers and celery into skillet.
Saute over medium heat until soft.
Add flour; stir into vegetables.
Add tomato sauce and water to vegetable mixture. Cook on low heat for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve Creole mixture over rice for a tasty meal!

title: cream cheese pecan pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 egg, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt in small bowl until thick and creamy.
Set aside.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Cream cream cheese.
Stir in next 5 ingredients until well mixed.
Spread on flour tortillas (approximately 1/4-inch thick) and roll up.
Chill until firm.
Slice the rolls approximately 1/2-inch.
Will fill 4 to 6 large tortillas.

title: green cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 325° in preheated oven in greased Bundt for 30 minutes.
Let cool for 30 minutes and invert on plate.

title: co-kerry cream
directions: Press seed into cream cheese on all sides and place on serving dish.
Pour soy sauce over cheese until sauce covers bottom of dish.
Let set at room temperature for 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: cream of wheat cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together.
Fold in 1 large container Cool Whip.
Fills 2 graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: old fashion sourdough starter
directions: Peel and boil potatoes in 3 cups water.
Strain off 2 cups water.
Mix potato water, flour and sugar.
Beat until smooth. Cover and set in warm place for several days until mixture sours and becomes bubbly (an oven with a pilot light is a good place). Then place in the refrigerator.

title: knot cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Make a well and add butter, cream cheese, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jill's peachy fruitcake
directions: In a very large mixing bowl, stir together flour and brown sugar, soda and spices.
Stir in fruits, peels, nuts and raisins. Add peaches, milk, mincemeat and brandy.
Mix well.
Turn into 2 greased and floured loaf pans or 5 mini loaf pans.
Bake 2 hours or until done at 300°.
Remove from pans.
Wrap in clear wrap or foil and store in a cool place.
Add ribbon or holly or miniature bottle of brandy to be used for soaking cloth by lucky recipient.

title: chocolate turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels with butter and milk until smooth. Make mix as directed on package. Pour 1/2 of cake batter in greased and lightly floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove and cool (cake will be a thick liquidy consistency) for 10 to 15 minutes. Pour caramel mixture on and spread, then sprinkle with chips and pecans. Pour rest of batter and smooth. Bake for another 30 to 45 minutes. Test with toothpick. Chips will not melt.

title: mom's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; blend in melted butter, flour, vanilla, salt, sugar and syrup.
Sprinkle some nuts on bottom of unbaked crust.
Mix the rest in with the syrup mixture.
Gently pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake in a hot oven at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce the heat to 325° for 45 minutes longer.
Cool.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream together the butter, eggs and sugar.
Add the milk.
Sift the dry ingredients together.
Mix all together with grated rind of lemon.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir juice of 1 lemon and 1/2 cup sugar together and pour over bread while hot.
Allow to soak in.

title: dirt dessert
directions: In one bowl, mix 3 1/2 cups milk and pudding.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, margarine, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add pudding mixture.
Layer 1/3 cookie crumbs, 1/2 pudding, 1/3 cookie crumbs, 1/2 pudding and 1/3 cookie crumbs.
Can be garnished with gummy worms and plastic flowers.

title: cabbage rolls(malfoof)
directions: Core and parboil cabbage until limp.
Cut leaves in half, removing the ribs.
Set oven at 400°.
Combine all ingredients except cabbage leaves, tomato paste and water.
Place a heaping tablespoonful of the filling in a leaf lengthwise.
Fold the outside edges 1/2 inch towards center and roll.
Arrange in a casserole dish or small roaster.

title: chocolate zucchini cake with custard sauce
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat sugar, oil and margarine. Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla; mix well.

Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves; gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in zucchini, chocolate chips and almonds. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to wire rack.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and fluffy.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Add flour.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Continue beating egg white mixture until they hold firm peaks.
Fold into egg yolk batter. Pour into ungreased tube baking pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until light brown.
When done, invert on a glass bottle until cool.

title: dilled potatoes vinaigrette
directions: Cut potatoes into quarters and steam for 7 to 10 minutes, until tender.
In a bowl, whisk together mustard, vinegar, wine and salt to taste.
Add oil in a stream while whisking and whisk until emulsified.
Add warm potatoes and toss gently with the dressing and dill.
Add pepper to taste.
Coat well.
Add pepper to taste.
Coat well.
Let stand at least 30 minutes, tossing occasionally.
May be made 1 day ahead and served cold.

title: "germs"(a.k.a. "hello dollies")
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
On top of margarine, spread graham cracker crumbs evenly.
Over crumbs, sprinkle coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour condensed milk evenly over ingredients.
Do not stir.
Place in a 350° oven; cook for 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix squash and jalapeno peppers.
Add eggs and flour (you may need a little more flour).
Mix well. Drop by large spoon on a griddle like pancakes.
Brown on both sides.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and pudding mixes according to the package directions. Assemble in a large deep glass bowl.
Break up cake in pieces (about the size of large egg) and layer in the bottom of the bowl. Spread with half of the vanilla pudding.
Sprinkle with half of the crushed pineapple.
Layer with one can of cherry pie filling.
Cover with a generous amount of cool whip and sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Repeat with a second layer of each, finishing with cool whip sprinkled with nuts and cherries.
Cover with saran wrap and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: pea salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Then in a jar, mix together the sugar, salad oil and vinegar. Shake well. Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps real well until it's all gone.

title: marinated roast beef
directions: Pierce meat with fork about 20 times.
In 2 1/2-quart bowl, mix 1 cup beer (reserve remaining beer), oil, lemon juice, onion, garlic, bay leaf, thyme, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Place meat in a plastic bag and pour the marinade over meat.
Refrigerate, turning occasionally (or at least 6 hours, but no longer than 24 hours).
Remove roast from marinade (reserve marinade)

title: spam and cheese sandwich spread
directions: Grate Spam and onion.
Add cheese.
Moisten with soup.
Spread on toast then broil until cheese has melted.
Makes several open faced sandwiches.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in shortening.
Add seasoning and tomatoes.
Cover; simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add kidney beans.
Pour mixture into greased 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cornbread batter.
Spread with wet knife.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth, drain but don't rinse.
Chop up turkey or chicken and add to spaghetti.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Mix a little cold water with corn meal.
Stir into boiling water.
Add salt and butter.
Stir often.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Pour into a cake or bread pans.
Let cool.
Slice and fry for breakfast.
Serve with liverwurst and apple butter.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Arrange banana slices on bottom of crust; set aside.
Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat with wire whisk for 1 minute, or until well blended.
Pour mixture at once into crust. Cover with whipped topping.
Refrigerate 3 hours, or until set.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool slightly and add frozen orange juice, stirring to melt.
Chill until slightly syrupy and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into rectangular 7 x 12-inch glass pan or use individual molds.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream margarine and the next 2 ingredients at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg whites and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Press cookie dough into the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Yields 4 dozen (serving size is 1 bar).

title: frozen peach dessert
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter. Stir in crumbs, reserving 1/4 cup for garnish. Pat remaining crumbs on bottom of buttered 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Set aside.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Combine ham and 3/4 cup of cheese.
Alternate layers of noodles and ham and cheese in greased, 1-quart baking dish.
Mix soup, milk and curry powder; pour over noodles.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and dot with butter.
Bake in 375° oven 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, buttermilk, hot water, sugar and oil.
Add eggs last; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: grandma fore's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan or Bundt pan. Mix together dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream sugar and butter together with electric mixer.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Begin adding dry ingredients to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk, mixing well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks and gently fold into batter.
Pour batter into a tube pan or large Bundt pan (loaf pans may also be used, adjust baking times).
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake test done.

title: fish batter
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add 2/3 or less can of beer.
Drink rest!
Crumble up crackers.

title: raised donuts
directions: Mix water and yeast together and cool.
Heat milk and add remaining ingredients. Cool the milk and yeast mixtures to the same temperature and mix together.
Knead the dough together very well, place in a clean bowl, cover and let sit in a warm place to rise.
